1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. Be3 c6 5. h3
{ We are taking control over the g4-square. From here, we plan to carry out the move f4 which will give us a better version of the Austrian Attack. Additionally, the possibility of playing g4 is there, although this occurs less frequently. }
5... Nbd7 { Suggested by GM Marin and also the most played move. } 6. f4
{ The same plan like in the other lines. In order to punish Black's passive play, we must take full control of the center. }
6... b5
{ The Romanian GM tried this move himself back in 2004, but ended up losing badly. }
7. a3 { Once again this is a key move, taking control of the b4-square. } 7...
Nb6
{ By far the most played move and much better if you ask me. Black's idea is to play d5 followed by Ne4, when he will get decent play on the light squares. }
8. Bd3
{ Not common, but it looks like the most accurate move as White takes full control of the e4-square. }
8... Bg7 9. Nf3 O-O 10. O-O Nc4
{ Is now met by   10...Bb7  11.Qe1  Yet again, the queen is heading to the beautiful h4-square.  11...a5  12.f5  Opening the diagonal and getting ready to attack.  12...Qc7  13.Qh4  Nbd7  14.Bh6  The attack plays itself.  14...Rfe8  15.Rae1  Simple natural moves have already given us a completely dominating position. There's no need to look any further, as Black's position is in ruins. I will let you click through the rest of the game if you want to, but the theory section ends.  15...b4  16.Nd1  c5  17.Bxg7  Kxg7  18.e5  White is finally breaking through.  18...Ng8  19.Ng5  Nh6  20.fxg6  f6  21.Ne6+  Black resigned as mate is impossible to avoid, along with decisive loss of material. Fluvia Poyatos,J - Szalontay,M Figueres 2013. }
11. Bc1
{ It's not worth it to give the light-squared bishop for the knight on c4 that looks annoying, but it doesn't do much. If necessary, we can also chase it away with b3. }
11... Bb7
{ 11...a5  Some strong players tried this, when we will once again play  12.Qe1  Nd7  And here, a simple novelty is  13.a4+-  Black will lose a pawn, when it will take a miracle to save the game. }
12. Qe1 { A nice square for the queen. } 12... a6 13. e5
{ It's time to strike! } 13... Nd5 14. Nxd5 cxd5 15. e6 f5 16. g4
{ Black's wall won't hold. } 16... Qb6 17. c3
{ The Ukrainian GM had shown excellent technique and won convincingly in Solodovnichenko,Y - Karaokcu,E Konya 2016. }
