[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter − Alekhine, Scandi, Philidor"]
[Black "Philidor Endgame 6…Bb4"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5
{ This is the best and most common way to reach the Philidor Defense, named after the famous 18th century player Francois-André Danican Philidor. }
4. dxe5 dxe5 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 6. Bc4
{ The game has barely started, and an endgame is already here. } 6... Bb4
{ The most active way of defending the pawn is to attack our pawn on e4. } 7.
Bxf7
{ It's a lot more common to play  7.Bd2  , but the text move was played by Stockfish against Leela, so I trust his judgement. }
7... Rf8 8. Bb3 Nxe4 9. Ne2 { Black has to play accurately here. } 9... Bf5
{ An active post for the c8-bishop, and the most played move in the position.   9...Rxf2?  Loses after  10.Ng3!  Black's king will be too exposed and our forces far too strong. The line goes  10...Nxg3  11.hxg3  Rxg2  12.Bg5+  Ke8  13.O-O-O  A pawn on h7 is now hanging, Rd8 is a threat, Nb5/d5 is in the air, etc. Black is completely busted.  13...Nc6  14.Nb5  Black can only defend the pawn on c7 by playing 14... Ba5, when 15. Rxh7 is the end for Black.   9...Nxf2?!  Is good for us after  10.Rf1  Ng4  11.Bg5+  Ke8  12.Rxf8+  Bxf8  13.O-O-O  White was close to winning in Korneev,O - Torres Ventosa,P Linares 2013, as Black is incredibly passive. }
10. Be3 { We will develop normally and castle queenside. } 10... Nd7 11. O-O-O
Nxc3
{ Black has to neutralize our pressure, otherwise he will be in deep trouble. }
12. Nxc3 c6 { Covering the d5-square and freeing the c7-square for the king. }
13. Ne2
{ The knight will be better placed on g3, while we can also chase away the bishop on b4 by playing c3. }
13... Kc7 14. Ng3 Bg6 15. c3 Be7 16. Bc2
{ A clever move, trading Black's strong light-squared bishops. Now the e4-square will be controlled by us, when our slight edge is clear as the e5-pawn is a permanent weakness. }
16... Bxc2 17. Kxc2 Nf6 { Black tries to centralize the knight. } 18. Rhe1 Nd5
19. f3
{ An improvement over  19.Ne4  which happened in Mastrovasilis, D - Yakhubboev, N Batumi 2018. }
19... Rad8 20. Bd2
{ Black has an unpleasant endgame as the pawn on e5 will remain a weakness until the end of the game. c4-Bc3 is a plan for the near future, along with Nh1-f2-d3/g4. We can also jump to h5 to provoke Black into weakening himself even more. }
