[Result "*"]

1. e4 g5
{ This speculative pawn launch, known as the Borg Defense, can't objectively be good, but I will take a deep dive into it for the sake of completion and satisfying Basman and all his fans @@StartBracket@@Michael Basman is an IM from England who is known for playing very rare lines, giving him a sort of legendary status@@EndBracket@@. The reason for the name 'Borg,' is the fact that this is a reversed Grob. 'Borg' is 'Grob' spelled backwards. This took me several weeks to realize. }
2. d4 { As usual, we will seize control of the center. } 2... Bg7
{ Black is baiting us into taking the unprotected pawn. Objectively, White is winning, but it isn't as easy as it looks. As a matter of fact, I have won several blitz games against lower-rated players with this funky line. }
3. Bxg5 { We will take the bait. } 3... c5
{ This is the only challenging response. Black is utilizing the fact that our bishop no longer supports the pawn on b2, while the Queen will be placed on the b6-square soon, applying pressure on d4 & b2. }
4. c3
{ I like this move, protecting the pawn on d4 while blocking the diagonal. }
4... cxd4 5. cxd4 Qb6 6. Nf3 Nc6
{ This is the most challenging response, as  6...Qxb2  is met by  7.Nbd2  , with Nc4 looming in the air. Black will have to return to b6, but giving White so much activity will surely lead to disaster. }
7. Nc3
{ Developing the knight looks good, as we are well prepared to meet both pawn captures. }
7... Nxd4 8. Nd5 { Attacking the queen while also aiming for the c7-square. }
8... Qxb2 9. Rc1 { It's important to guard the c2-square. } 9... Nxf3+ 10. gxf3
{ Opening up the g-file for our rook. } 10... Kf8 11. Rg1
{ We have a tremendous amount of activity which makes it really difficult for Black to find a move. }
11... e6
{ Chasing away the knight is logical and a very 'human' way to play.   11...b6  12.Bd2  Guarding our king, while also having ideas like Rxg7, followed by Bc3!  12...Bb7  13.Rxg7!  This tactical blow works.  13...Qxg7  14.Bc3  f6  15.Nc7+-  White wins, as Black can't defend the pawn on  d7  with  15...Re8  , due to  16.Qxd7  Without the pawn, the weaknesses around Black's king will decide the game. }
12. Rc2 { We will gladly take the endgame. } 12... Qa1 13. Qxa1 Bxa1 14. Nc7
Rb8 15. Bf4 { Threatening to take on e6, followed by Bxb8. } 15... e5 16. Bd2
{ There is no good way to defend against the threat of Bb4+, followed by Nd5. }
