8... Nf4 9. Be4 Bxe4 10. Nxe4
{ Black already resigned in Dobronravov, O-Krivoshapko,A Omsk 2009. The resignation might seem slightly premature, so I will give a few more moves. }
10... Ng6 11. d5 bxc4 12. h4 Nxh4 13. Bg5 Nxf3+ 14. Qxf3
{ Black's terrible development gives him severe problems. } 14... Qb6 15. Rad1
{ Placing our rook on the open file while threatening to take on e6, followed by a knight jump to d6. }
15... Ra7 16. Rfe1
{ This is the perfect set-up. Qh5 will follow next, when Black won't be able to prevent us from taking on e6, followed by either Rd8+ or Nd6+. }
16... h6 17. Qh5 Rc7 18. dxe6 Qxe6 19. Nd6+
{ Black loses the queen and the game. } *

