{ Pinning the knight is a logical way for Black to fight against our center, with Nf6 and c5/ d5 coming. This set-up is not so easy to play against, and I even remember struggling with White against a lower-rated player in a rapid game. }
5. Ne2
{ When diving deeply into this line, it became clear to me that this move was the best. One of the huge advantages with Nge2 is that we can recapture back on c3 with our knight, avoiding a bad pawn structure. We can gain an attack rather quickly with Nf4, followed by Qg4 and Nh5.   5.Nh3!?  is a very interesting move here as well, just not as good as our move. }
5... d5
{ I personally think this is Black's best bet, gaining at least some sort of control in the center. However, the resulting position is a bad French. }
6. e5
{ Taking away the f6 square for the knight, while also closing the diagonal for the bishop on b7. }
6... c5
{ Is a natural way to continue, gaining more activity and pressure against our center. }
7. a3
{ There is no time to waste. We can't allow Black to take our pawn on d4, followed by Bxc3, when our pawns will be very weak. }
7... Bxc3+ 8. Nxc3 a6 { Black should not allow us to play Nb5-Nd6. } 9. Qg4
{ A standard move, attacking g7. } 9... g6
{ is met by the typical   9...Kf8  might be better, as the Black squares aren't so weak like after g6.  10.b3!?  I like this move, avoiding the c4 move which would eliminate our bishop from the diagonal.  10...cxd4  11.Ne2  Nc6  12.f4  We are clearly better. A plan is to simply O-O followed by b4-Bb2. Once we have castled, we can start aiming for the f5-break, blasting up the kingside. Black doesn't have any good plans, so practically I'd say it is close to lost, since our plan is rather simple to execute. }
10. h4 { Black can't allow us to play h5, so he has to do so himself. } 10...
h5 11. Qg3
{ The dark squares are incredibly weak. Bg5 will come, when we will someday be able to put our bishop on f6. I like the idea of also moving the knight to b1-d2-f3. Removing the knight from the c3-square gives us the possibility of guarding the pawn on d4 with c3. The objective evaluation is as high as 1.70, but for a human being, I'd say it is only close to winning for now. }
