7... Be7
{ Has been played a decent amount of times, but it loses by force after } 8.
Qg4
{ The queen is well placed on g4. Not only does it target the pawn on g7, but it greatly reinforces the effect of a knight sacrifice on e6. }
8... g6
{ 8...g5  A 2193 beat a 2300 with player with this move, but it wasn't due to the opening, that's for sure.  9.Nxe6  This is a nice resource.  9...fxe6  10.Qh5+  Kf8  11.f4  White will open up the f-file when Black's king is doomed.  11...Qe8  12.Qh6+  Kg8  13.Qxe6+  Qf7  14.Qh3  O-O comes next when Black won't survive the attack. }
9. Nxe6 { Once again! } 9... fxe6 10. Bxg6+ hxg6 11. Qxg6+ Kf8 12. Bh6+ Rxh6
13. Qxh6+
{ We've sacrificed 3 pieces for a rook and three pawns. This might seem bad, however I think our attack is just too dangerous. }
13... Kf7 14. Qh7+ Kf8 15. O-O-O
{ h4-Rh3 or Rd3-Rf3 may follow very soon. Black hung on 9 more moves before he resigned in Manninen,H - Schulz,B ICCF email 2017. However, we can stop here as Black can't stop our rooks from delivering a devastating blow. }
