Nxf6+ Nxf6 25. exf6 { Re7+ is a deadly threat, when the best defense is... }
25... d2+ 26. Kxd2 { After  26.Qxd2  the f6-pawn hangs. } 26... Rf7 27. Re6
{ We need to protect the pawn on d6 and make sure that the queen stays out of the game. Black can still win the pawn after }
27... Nc4+ 28. Kc1 Nxd6 { But our king is no longer in danger. } 29. Rhe1
{ Is a simple way to continue when Re7 will come, often followed by g5. Black's king is very weak, and I can't see how he will survive. }
