[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. c4 Nb6 5. f4
{ Here we go. We keep our center intact, aiming for a massive space advantage. A massive pro with this system is that Black does not have many decent options at his disposal, as we soon shall see. }
5... dxe5 6. fxe5 c5
{ Undermining the center with c5 is a typical and rather tricky way to play, so we must be prepared. }
7. d5 e6
{ Going for a Benoni-like structure doesn't work too well here. The better move is  7...g6  which will lead to 6...g6 . }
8. Nc3 exd5 9. cxd5 c4
{ Has been by far the most popular move, and the only way to justify giving away the center. }
10. d6
{ Black's point is seen after   10.Nf3  Bb4!  when he gets some pressure against our center. This gives White a decent advantage too, but it is extremely unnecessary.  d6  takes away all of Black's fun, when the position is objectively lost already due to our massive space advantage. }
10... Nc6 11. Bf4 g5
{ Is the best practical choice, as it complicates the game with a queen sacrifice. }
12. Ne4
{ This is the only move that leads to an advantage.   12.Nb5  has been played sometimes, but the queen sacrifice is significantly stronger after  12...gxf4  13.Nc7+  Qxc7  . Black will follow up with Bb4+ and O-O quickly, when our king is stuck in the center. }
12... gxf4 13. Nf6+ Qxf6 14. exf6
{ Black has sacrificed a queen for two minor pieces, but it is not so easy at it looks. We haven't completed our development yet, and our pawns are quite weak. If we are not careful, Black could get a lot of counterplay after Be6-O-O-O. }
14... Be6 15. Qh5
{ This is by far the best move and the best way to encounter Black's idea. We are aiming to castle ourselves, while the queen is also really well placed on h5. It is difficult for Black to attack it, while it also supports a potential Nf3-Ng5 jump. }
15... Bxd6 16. O-O-O O-O-O 17. Nf3 { We're aiming for Ng5. } 17... h6
{ Preventing the jump seems like the most reasonable way to fight. } 18. Be2 c3
{ A decent attempt to complicate matters. } 19. Nd4
{ We want to trade pieces. } 19... cxb2+ 20. Kb1 Nd5
{ This may look scary, but we are well prepared. } 21. Nxe6 fxe6 22. Rxd5
{ I like getting rid of the knight on d5, but there are other moves as well. }
22... exd5 23. Bf3
{ We have everything under control and I can't see how Black will survive here due to our really powerful passed pawn on f6. }
