{ Looks awful for Black. If Nxc4 comes, we'll respond with Qe2 followed by e6. Remember that it won't be possible to capture the pawn on d5, because Rd1 will come when the queen can't move due to the mate on d8. A correspondence game was seen here, which I will let you play through. Our theory section stops here, though.   12...Bxc3+  13.bxc3  O-O   The engine has improved and prefers  14.O-O  here, but the Main Line is still strong of course.  14.Qd3  Qa4  15.O-O  Qxc4  16.Qxf5  Nxd5  17.e6  f6  18.Nd2  Ne7  19.Nxc4  Nxf5  20.Rxf5  fxg5  21.Rxc5  Rf6  22.Rc8+  Rf8  23.Rxf8+  Kxf8  24.Rf1+  Ke7  25.Rf7+  Kxe6  26.Rf8  b5  27.Ne3  Kd7  28.c4  bxc4  29.Nxc4  Kc7  30.Rf7+  Kc6  31.Rxg7  Nd7  32.Rxg5  Re8  33.Rg7  Re1+  34.Kf2  Ra1  35.a3  Nb6  36.Ne5+  Kd6  37.Nf7+  Kd5  38.h4  Ra2+  39.Kg1  h5  40.Rg5+  Ke6  41.Nh6  Rxa3  42.Rxh5  Ra4  43.g3  Nd7  44.Kg2  Ne5  45.Rg5  a5  46.Rg8  Re4  47.Re8+  Kd5  48.Ng8  Re2+  49.Kh3  a4  50.Nf6+  Kc6  51.Ra8  Kb5  52.Nd5  Rc2  53.Rb8+  Ka5  54.Ra8+  Kb5  55.Rb8+  Ka5  56.Re8  Nd3  57.h5  Rc5  58.Nf6  Rc6  59.Ng4  a3  60.Ne5  Nf2+  61.Kg2  Rc2  62.Kf3  Kb4  63.h6  Nh3  64.Rb8+  Kc3  65.Kg4  Rh2  66.Rc8+  Kb3  67.Nd3  Nf2+  68.Nxf2  Rxh6  69.Nd3  Rf6  70.Rb8+  Kc3  71.Nc1  Kc2  72.Na2  Rf1  73.Nb4+  Kc1  74.Kh4  Rh1+  75.Kg5  Kb2  76.Kf4  Rf1+  77.Ke3  Rf7  78.g4  Rg7  79.Kf3  Kb3  80.Nd5+  Kc4  81.Ne3+  Kc3  82.Ra8  Kb3  83.Nc2  a2  84.Nb4  Rf7+  85.Kg3  White finally won in Bernal Varela, N Rain, R ICCF email 2017. }
