1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. c4 Nb6 5. f4
{ Here we go. We keep our center intact, aiming for a massive space advantage. A massive pro with this system is that Black does not have many decent options at his disposal, as we soon shall see. }
5... dxe5 6. fxe5 Nc6 7. Be3 Bf5 8. Nc3 e6 9. Nf3
{ We have arrived at the Main Position in the Four Pawns Attack. Black has a wide arsenal of options here, and all of them have been played 200+ times. }
9... Be7 10. d5
{ This used to be the Main Move, and still is the most played move in the position, but modern engines claim a forced draw. It should be mentioned that the path is narrow for Black, however I expect Black to be prepared. }
10... exd5
{ 10...Nb4?  This losing move is played over 200 times, by strong and weak players alike. The reason why is that we can play Rc1 here, instead of Nd4 like in the main line. This is highly significant, don't ask me why :@@EndBracket@@ }
11. cxd5 Nb4 12. Nd4 Bd7
{ 12...Bg6?  Yet another way to lose, played by 78 players. } 13. e6
{ The most critical test.   13.Qf3!?  c5  14.dxc6  Bxc6!  15.Nxc6  bxc6  16.Qe4  O-O  17.Be2  N6d5  18.Bf2  Nxc3  19.bxc3  Qd5 = }
13... fxe6 14. dxe6 Bc6
{ I looked at several moves here, but it all ends in a draw. } 15. a3
{ This looks more promising.   15.Qg4  Bh4+  16.g3  Bxh1  17.O-O-O  O-O  18.gxh4  Qf6!  19.Be2  The 'winning' attempt.   19.Bg5  Qxf1  20.Rxf1  Rxf1+  21.Nd1!  Nd3+  22.Kc2  Ne1+  23.Kc1  Nd3+ =  19...Bd5!  20.Bg5  Qe5  21.e7  Rfe8  22.h5  h6  23.Bh4  Kh8  24.a3  Na2+  25.Nxa2  Bxa2  26.Nf5  Qc5+  27.Kd2  Qa5+  28.b4  Qe5  29.Rg1  Qb2+  30.Ke1  Nd5  31.Qxg7+  Qxg7  32.Rxg7  Bb1  33.Bg3  Bxf5  34.Be5 = }
15... Bh4+ 16. g3 Bxh1 17. axb4 Bf6 18. Qg4 O-O 19. O-O-O
{ Black is on a tight rope here. } 19... Qe8
{ 19...Nd5?  20.Bc4  Nxe3  21.e7+  Kh8  22.exd8=Q  Rfxd8  23.Qh5  Nxc4  24.Ne6  Rxd1+  25.Qxd1+-  White will easily pick off the minor pieces and bring home the point. }
20. Bd3 Bg2 21. Nf5 h5 22. Nh6+ Kh8 23. Qf5 g6 24. Qxg6 Qxg6 25. Bxg6
{ The engines say 0.00, but the game is not over yet. Pretty cool lines all in all, but it is extremely unnecessary to venture into these kinds of complications when the Main Move is such a good choice. }
