15... Rd7
{ Sort of a waiting move, but it opens up the possibility of playing Qd8 for instance, pressuring against d4. }
16. h3 h6 17. c5
{ Not necessary at all, but I like the approach. The usual slow-improving move of  17.Qc1  was also good of course. }
17... Nd5 18. Bg1
{ The bishop is heading to h2, when we will gain decent control of the vulnerable e5-square. }
18... Qd8 19. Bh2
{ We continue with our plan. The modern engine prefers  19.Rde1  , which is also good of course. }
19... Rdf7 { Black aims to gain some counterplay on the f-file. } 20. Bb5
{ Proceeding with our plan.  20.Rfe1  for example was also good. } 20... Bg6
21. Qe2 Qe8 22. Rfe1 Re7 23. Ne4
{ White had a fine position in Byrne,M - Bradney,R ICCF email 2017. Black is rather cramped. An attempt of playing Bh5 is simply met by g4. }
