11. O-O Rd8 12. b3
{ I analyzed this position deeply, and things were much harder than I had expected. First of all, I wanted to go for  12.Ng5  , but the game gets rather complicated after  12...Nxc4!  Then, I decided to analyze  12.c5  , but I honestly feel that Black's light-square control is solidified in the position. See for instance the game Hoeppenstein, M - Mulde, R GER email 2009. }
12... Be7 { Developing the bishop is sensible. } 13. Qe1
