[Black "2...Nd5 (5...dxe5 6...Nc6 9...Bg4 8)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. c4 Nb6 5. f4
{ Here we go. We keep our center intact, aiming for a massive space advantage. A massive pro with this system is that Black does not have many decent options at his disposal, as we soon shall see. }
5... dxe5 6. fxe5
{ Before we move to the Main tabiya of the Four Pawn Attack, I just want to quickly highlight what happens if Black chooses to go for a set-up without Nc6, or delays e6. }
6... Nc6 7. Be3 Bf5 8. Nc3 e6 9. Nf3
{ We have arrived at the Main Position in the Four Pawns Attack. Black has a wide arsenal of options here, and all of them have been played 200+ times. }
9... Bg4
{ This move has been the second most popular move in the position, with the idea of taking on f3 next. We will be forced to take with the g-pawn, due to our pawn on d4 will be hanging. }
10. Be2 { It's best to keep it simple. } 10... Bxf3
{ This is why Black played Bg4, so it is not surprising that it is the most popular continuation. }
11. gxf3 Qh4+
{ Has been seen in over 250 games, when we have a pleasant choice between an attack or a better endgame. Alternatives exist, but they are not impressive.  11...Be7  can simply be met by  O-O  , when our pawn on  f3  is an addition to our position as  f4  is possible, strengthening our center.  11...Qd7  can be met by  Qd2  , when we will castle long.  11...Bb4  is an attempt to play similar to the  9. Bb4-lines, but again I think our f-pawn just helps our center. Remember that the light-squared bishop is absent, making our bishop pair rather strong. We may also put our king on the h1-square when we can utilize the f-file for attacking purposes. }
12. Bf2 Qf4 13. c5 Nd5 14. Nxd5 exd5 15. O-O
{ Black will be met by a very powerful attack when he decides to go for long castling. Be7 might be played when we can go for Qb3-Qc3-b4-b5. If long castling is played right away, we can simply start throwing our pawns at the black king with b4.   I will mention that  15.Qb3  followed by Qe3 is an alternative, trading queens, but O-O is much stronger. There is no need to trade queens as our attack is significantly stronger. }
