{ White's score from this position has been fantastic, and it is not surprising. It doesn't seem like Black has any good plans here, while our plan of one day playing d5 is simple to execute. There are many different approaches to this position, and they're all good, but I like the move }
10. Qb3 Qb6
{ 10...Qc7  gives us  11.Bf4  for free, since we will win the rook on a8 if Black takes the bishop.  With   10...Qc8  I like the simple approach of  11.Bf4  , when play can continue with  11...O-O  . After  12.Rad1  , we're getting ready for the d5-break in the near future.  12...Nbd7  with  13.g4!  Bg6  14.Nh4  Rd8  15.Nxg6  hxg6  16.Bf3  From here we should continue preparing the plan of d5 with Rfe1, Kg2, etc as we have all the time in the world. The text move is probably best, when we will get a very pleasant endgame after }
