[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "5. Scandinavian (1...d5) Minor Sidelines"]
[Black "2...Nf6 (3...Nxd5 4...Nb6 2) "]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Nf6
{ This is the first branch of the Scandinavian Defense. Black's idea is to avoid the time loss of capturing the pawn with the queen. }
3. d4 Nxd5 4. c4 { We will keep occupying the center. } 4... Nb6
{ This is Black's most active response which has seen the light of day over 7500 times!  4...Nf6  has been seen around 2000, just to compare. }
5. Nf3 Bg4
{ Pinning the knight is certainly logical, but that doesn't make it a great move. However, this is due to concrete reasons as we soon shall see. }
6. c5
{ Attacking the knight on c5 is the most concrete approach to the position. }
6... N6d7 7. Be2
{ Removing the pin while developing our pieces. Black has two main moves here, but the position remains very uncomfortable to play in practice. White has a very good score from here, while neither Stockfish or Leela survived with the black pieces when this opening was given in the Top Computer Chess Championship TCEC. }
7... Nc6
{ Was tried by Leela, which means that we should take a look. Black wants to open up the possibility of playing e5, attacking our pawns. }
8. Be3 e5
{ Only one human game continued with this move. The rest preferred to play   8...e6  , but this is just too passive when a simple way to proceed would be  9.h3  . }
9. O-O
{ It's important that we get our king out of the way. Now a forced sequence was }
9... Bxf3 10. Bxf3 exd4 11. Bxd4 Nxd4 12. Qxd4 Nxc5
{ 12...Bxc5  didn't work as the pawn on g7 would be hanging. } 13. Qc3
{ Re1 is now a move Black should watch out for, when the pawn on g7 or b7 would fall. }
13... Qc8 { Defending the b7-pawn. } 14. Nd2 Ne6
{ Leela defends the g7-pawn, so she can develop the bishop. } 15. Qb3
{ An important move. Not only is b7 under attack, but we could also pin the knight with Bg4 next, followed up with Nf3-Ng5 , or Rfe1. }
15... Nd4 16. Rfe1+ Be7 17. Qc4
{ Black's position is like a fish out of the water. Castling won't be possible due to the bishop hanging on e7 , so the king will be forced to move to f8 . From here a simple plan is to double the rooks on the e-file, which Stockfish does next. We can leave it here, but I will leave some more moves as a clickable.   17...c5  18.Re3  b5  19.Qc3  Nxf3+  20.Nxf3  Kf8  21.Rae1  Bf6  22.Ne5  h5  23.Qd3  Bxe5  24.Rxe5  Kg8  25.Re7  Leela kept fighting for 40 more moves, but perished in the end in Stockfish 202006170741 - LCZero v0.25.1-svjio-t60-3972 TCEC 2020. I doubt a human would last long, though. }
