{ We do not need to do anything extraordinary here. The bishop pair is ours while we have a massive space advantage. }
10... a5 { Stockfish wanted to grab some space. } 11. Bf4 Be7 12. Na3
{ I really like what Leela is doing, putting a knight on c4. } 12... O-O 13.
Nc4 Nf6 14. a3 Nbd7 15. Re1
{ Our position is just fantastic. Black needs to worry about us placing a piece on d6 , while we have other ideas like Rc1-Rc3-Rb3, attacking b7 . Rb1-b4-b5 is also a good plan. Stockfish didn't manage to save the game either, when the game went Nd5   15.Bd5  cxd5  16.Nd6  Bxd6  17.Bxd6  Re8  18.b3  h6  19.Qd3  Ra6  20.b4  Nb6  21.b5  Ra8  22.a4  White was strategically completely winning in LCZero v0.25.1-svjio-t60-3972 3813 -Stockfish 202006170741 TCEC 2020. The game went on for over a 100 more moves, but Stockfish couldn't save the position. }
