[Result "*"]

1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Nf6
{ This is the first branch of the Scandinavian Defense. Black's idea is to avoid the time loss of capturing the pawn with the queen. }
3. d4 Nxd5 4. c4 { We will keep occupying the center. } 4... Nb6
{ This is Black's most active response which has seen the light of day over 7500 times! }
5. Nf3 g6
{ The most popular move, for good reason. The bishop will be better placed on g7 than on e7 as it attacks our pawn on d4. Besides, the pawn on g6 blocks the b1-h7 diagonal, so the king won't be vulnerable. This may sound appealing, but I think Black is biting the bullet with this line. The arising positions tend to lean towards a rather passive and sad game, much due to our fantastic central control and active pieces. }
6. a4 { I really like this move. } 6... a5
{ Preventing us from playing a5 is the most logical way to play. } 7. c5
{ It looks like to me that we get a good version of the Main Line. The pawn on a5 weakens the square on b6 which is an advantage in several lines. }
7... Nd5 8. Bc4
{ Black needs to proceed with care now that Qb3 is in the air. } 8... Bg7 9.
Qb3 { Black can defend the knight in two ways. } 9... c6
{ This is better as we don't get Bg5 with a tempo. } 10. Nc3 O-O 11. O-O
{ Black can approach this position in different ways. } 11... Nc7
{ Black wants to play Be6, trading the light-squared bishops. } 12. Ng5
{ We have a decent amount of good options, but I really like to put a stop to Black's plan. }
12... Qe8 13. Bf4 Nba6 14. Rfe1 h6
{ 14...Bxd4?  Loses to  15.Rad1!  Bg7  And now a forced sequence  16.Bxf7+!  Rxf7  17.Bxc7  Nxc7  18.Rd8!  The point.  18...Qxd8  19.Qxf7+  Kh8  20.Rxe7+-  We will win back the missing piece with a winning endgame. }
15. Nf3 Be6 { Black has finally achieved his goal. } 16. Be5
{ We're clearly better because of our active pieces @@StartBracket@@I know, this is a theme throughout the entire chapter@@EndBracket@@. A plan forward is to double our rooks on the e-file with Re4-Rae1. Black is likely to take on c4, when our queen may even go to Qe2, achieving the Alekhine Battery. }
