1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qd8 4. d4 { Grabbing the center as we always do. }
4... Nf6
{ Other moves have been played here, but this logical move is by far the most popular in the position. Black has to play Nf6 at some point anyway, so other options are likely to transpose. }
5. Nf3 Bf5 6. Ne5
{ This reaction is extremely typical and a crucial idea to remember in the Scandinavian. Just like in the 3... Qe5+ line, we're aiming to harass the bishop with a subsequent g4-h4. }
6... c6 { Black hasn't closed the door on playing Be6 after g4. } 7. Bc4
