{ We will once again take control of the center. } 4... c6 5. Nf3 Bg4 6. h3
{ Sacrificing a pawn. } 6... Bxf3 7. Qxf3 Qxd4
{ The critical move.  7...Nf6  8.Bf4  will probably transpose. If the game continues  8...Qd8  9.O-O-O  e6  the brilliant move  10.d5!  wins, followed by  Bb5  , when White breaks through. This is rather beautiful, but a simple move like  10.Kb1  is also excellent for White as Black is extremely passive. }
