{ This move justifies the sacrifice. It's very important to have control of the square on c7, which we will soon see. The move  8.Be3  has the most popular move, but after  8...Qd8  White does not have a huge advantage. }
8... e5 { Has been played by former World Champion Anatoly Karpov. } 9. Bg5 Be7
10. Rd1 { Keeping up the pressure. } 10... Qb6 11. Bc4
{ 11.Ne4  is also good, along with many other moves. } 11... Nf6 12. Bxf6 gxf6
{ 12...Bxf6  would have lost to  13.Ne4  , when it's worth noting that Qb4+ is met by c3, as the bishop can't be captured due to the fork after Nd6+. Ivanchuk had done everything right so far in the game Ivanchuk, V - Karpov, A Cap d'Adge 2013, but here he should have played }
13. Qg4 { Preventing O-O. } 13... Qc7 14. Ne4
{ There were many good moves here, but I think this is the easiest solution. Black's king is stuck in the center. It's important to keep in mind that  14...Nd7  loses to  15.Bxf7!+  . }
