9. Rd1 Qb6
{ Stockfish prefers sacrificing an exchange with  9...Qf6  10.Nb5!  Rc8  11.Nc7+  Rxc7  , but this isn't critical as the queens will be exchanged, leaving us an exchange up.   9...Qb4  10.a3!  Removing Black's control of the c4-square, so we can place our bishop there.  10...Qxb2  11.Rxd7!  Striking while the iron is hot as we are far ahead in development.  11...Kxd7  12.Bc4  This is lethal for Black, who has no defense against O-O followed by Rb1.  12...Qa1+  This looks scary, but it loses to  13.Ke2!  Qxh1  14.Qd3+!  Ke8  15.Nb5!  Nc7 mate is now threatened.  15...e5  16.Nc7+  Ke7  17.Qe3+- }
