6. h3
{ White has usually played  6.Ne5  or  6.g3  , and both of them look decent enough for an edge if you ask me.  My suggestion is not seen so often. The idea isn't harder than the fact that it prevents the active move Bg4. }
6... Nbd7 { Is another alternative, but again, I think it's awfully passive. }
7. Bd3 { From here, Black can complete the development in two ways. } 7... e6
{ Does not look impressive to me. } 8. O-O Be7 9. Re1
