Bg7 7. Qd2 O-O 8. O-O-O
{ Black now needs to make an important decision, as indeed, there are many different ways to proceed. }
8... c5 { Is possible once again, when we should reply with } 9. Bf4 Qb6
{ This is the only alternative to   9...Qd8  , which would have transposed to 8...c5 in 3...Qd8 . Here we saw that  10.d5!  was good for White. }
10. Na4
{ 10.d5?  would lead to a terrible position after  10...Ne4!  , so this time we should grab the pawn. }
10... Qd8 11. dxc5
