11... Bd7 { The best defense. } 12. Bb5
{ Utilizing that Black can't capture our bishop. Black needs to hurry up before our play becomes overwhelming. }
12... Qc8
{ Black should get out of the pin. After something like  12...Nc6  a simple move is  13.h3  Black is almost out of moves as  13...a6  is too weakening, leaving a hole on b6 after the bishop moves to e2 or d3 . }
13. Qe2 Bxb5 14. Qxb5 Nc6 15. Rhe1
{ Black does not have enough compensation for the missing pawn. One could even argue that White is more active than Black, further reinforcing my claim. }
