Qd7 13. Rhe1
{ Taking control of the e-file, but more importantly, the e5-square. d5 is now a possibility, something Black has to watch out for. }
13... a6
{ Doesn't work, due to   13...Qf5  Looks like Black's best defense.  14.Bxc6  I like destroying Black's pawn structure.  14...bxc6  15.Nc3  Otherwise Ne4 would come.  15...Nd5  Black shouldn't allow us to play Re5.  16.g4  Qf3  Black should try to go for counterplay.  17.Qe2  Qxe2  18.Nxe2  Black's double pawns gives him an unpleasant endgame. The best way to get counterplay is to go for an e5-break by the means of  18...f6  19.Bd2  f5  Black is threatening to open up the f-file, so we must play  20.g5  e5  Black has finally achieved the desired e5-break.  21.dxe5  Bxe5  22.c4  Nb6  23.b3  Black's double pawns gives him an unpleasant endgame to defend. }
14. d5 { This was the point of our previous play. } 14... Ne5
