{ 9...Qxb2  is easily dealt with. One of the many good ways to proceed is  10.Na4  , when White will play Nc5 and Rb1 next. So far we've been following Mamedow, R - Carlsen, M chess24.com INT 2020, when }
10. Nh4
{ Would have been the right path forward. We're kicking back all of Black's pieces. }
10... Bg6 11. a3 Qb6 12. Na4 Qd8 13. Nxg6 hxg6 14. c4
{ We've gotten the bishop pair along with fantastic control in the center. Black's position is hopeless due to the lack of activity, and his forces won't be able to cope with a d5 break. }
