16... Qd8 17. Qa3
{ Threatening to take on e7 followed by Nd6+, winning an exchange. } 17... Ra8
18. Rad1
{ Black's only way forward is to play Nf6, when we can take on e7 followed by Nxf6+. Then we can start attacking Black's pawns by the means of Qc5. Black can't castle either, making the resulting position even worse. }
