[Result "*"]

1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qd6 4. d4
{ We will once again take control of the center. } 4... Nf6 5. Nf3 a6
{ This has been the most common move, which is not surprising. Black's idea is clear. Now that Nb5 is not a problem, he can easily start to apply pressure in the center. a6 also opens up the possibility of b5-Bb7, but Black has to be careful with that pawn launch as the pawn on b5 can be easily targeted by a4, as we've seen earlier. Black's plans are crystal clear and not easily dealt with by the unprepared player, so pay attention! }
6. g3
{ This move is rather effective, since it makes it possible to get a tempo on Black's queen with Bf4, while giving the f1-bishop a nice square on g2 where it will be rather effective. }
6... b5 { Black can definitely play with this deck. } 7. Bg2 Bb7 8. O-O e6 9.
Ne5 { Only for Black though, his concept sort of falls apart after this move. }
9... Bxg2 { 9...Qb6  has been played some times, but  10.d5  is crushing. } 10.
Kxg2
{ Ne5 has made both Qf3 and Bf4 possible, moves that will be rather annoying for Black. }
10... Be7 11. Qf3 Ra7
{ 11... c6 is easily handled by the means of Bf4, when Black is more or less forced to give up the pawn due to the threats of Ng6/ Nxf7. }
12. Bf4 Nd5
{ Two draws were played with this move, and it is indeed the best option. Black aims to get rid of our bishop, decreasing our pressure. Another option:   12...Qd8  13.Rfd1  Where White will soon open up the center with the breakthrough d5, when Black's rook on a7 will look really corny. }
13. a4
{ As I pointed out earlier, Black always has to watch our for this move. }
13... Nxf4+ 14. gxf4
{ This move is really clever because we are reinforcing our control of the e5-square. Now the pawn break of d5 might be possible, while we can even utilize the open g-file. }
14... b4 15. Ne4 Qxd4
{ Black can't afford to give us additional tempi.   15...Qd5  16.c4  bxc3  17.bxc3  O-O  18.Rab1  Nd7  19.Nc6  Attacking the rook on a7 and the bishop on e7. The knight can't be captured due to the discovery check on f6, winning the queen. }
16. Rad1 Qb6 17. Rg1 { Aiming to provoke a weakness in Black's kingside. }
17... g6 18. Qh3 { Now we can enter into Black's camp with Qh6-Qg7. } 18... O-O
{ Black may try to castle before it's too late, but his king is just too weak. }
19. Qh6 { Rd3 followed by Rh3 is deadly. } *

