{ There are a bunch of different set-ups we can go for, but I think the knight move is the most critical option. The Main Line gives Black a plethora of options, which will all be covered in this chapter. }
3... c5
{ This move is not good objectively, but we must be prepared against it. } 4.
dxc5 { Taking the bait is the most critical move. } 4... Bxc3+
{ The other alternative. Black hopes to make the game unbalanced with giving away this strong bishop for a damaged pawn structure. }
5. bxc3 Nf6
{ An interesting try, played particularly in online games by FM Storey,C and IM Barria Zuniga,D. }
6. e5 Ne4 7. Bc4
{ The only move that leads to more than just a small advantage. The point is that we create a counterattack, as Black's f7-pawn in particular, is vulnerable. }
