[Black "2...Bg7 (3...d5 2)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 g6 2. d4
{ As always we will take full control of the center if we get the chance. }
2... Bg7 { I'd say this move will be played against you 99/100 times... } 3.
Nc3
{ There are a bunch of different set-ups we can go for, but I think the knight move is the most critical option. The Main Line gives Black a plethora of options, which will all be covered in this chapter. }
3... d5
{ Is a highly interesting pawn sacrifice which could even be the best move in the position. Black's scheme is to develop quickly and regain the pawn at a later stage with Nbd7-Nb6. }
4. exd5
{ Taking the pawn is the best way to fight for an edge. The knight capture is interesting as well. Advancing with 4. e5 isn't the best way to go, as Black gets counterplay against our center with f6 and c5. }
4... Nf6 5. Bc4 Nbd7
{ Black should try to regain the pawn as fast as possible. } 6. Nf3
{ 6.Bg5  has been suggested in some books, but I believe Black is fine after  6...Nb6  7.Bxf6  Bxf6  8.Bb3  Now it's important for Black to force an endgame after  8...c6!  9.dxc6  Qxd4  10.Qxd4  Bxd4  11.Nge2  Bg7  12.Nd5  is now the most testing move, when Black has to play  12...Bxb2!  13.Nc7+  Kd8  14.cxb7  Bxb7  15.Nxa8  Bxa1  16.Nxb6  axb6  , which is a drawn endgame. }
6... Nb6 7. Bb3 a5
{ Has been twice as popular as  7...O-O  , but it's inaccurate. } 8. Na4
{ This strong move has only been played four times which forces Black to give us c4 with a tempo, giving us a strong center. }
8... Nbxd5 9. c4 Nb4 10. O-O
{ Black's position has now become rather passive due to our fantastic center. }
10... O-O 11. a3 Na6 12. h3 { A natural move as we prevent Bg4. } 12... c6 13.
Nc3 { The knight has done its job, so it's heading back to c3. } 13... Nc7 14.
Re1
{ White has played strong and logical moves, so the advantage has increased steadily. }
14... b5 { The best way to create counterplay. } 15. Ne5 Bb7 16. c5
{ A rather strong move, opening the diagonal for the bishop on b3, and making sure that the bishop on b7 will remain passive. }
16... Nfd5 17. Qf3 Ne6 18. Bxd5 cxd5
{ So far, White had played outstandingly in the game Rogers, J - Fernandez, D England 2018. Somehow, White played the move  19.c6?  where most of the advantage vanished. }
19. Nxb5 { Black is in dire straits. } *

