[White "10. Modern (1...g6) Minor Sidelines"]
[Black "2...Bg7 (3...Nc6)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 g6 2. d4
{ As always we will take full control of the center if we get the chance. }
2... Bg7 { I'd say this move will be played against you 99/100 times... } 3.
Nc3
{ There are a bunch of different set-ups we can go for, but I think the knight move is the most critical option. The Main Line gives Black a plethora of options, which will all be covered in this chapter. }
3... Nc6
{ It's quite uncommon to put the knight on c6 so early, but it has been played by some strong players, in particular GM Attila Czebe. }
4. Be3 { This is the easiest way to deal with Black's shenanigans. } 4... d5 5.
Nxd5
{ The best move. After the more common  5.exd5  , Black can play  5...Nb4  , when our advantage is close to getting wiped out already. }
5... e6 6. Nc3 Nxd4 { Black's point with the d5-break. } 7. f4
{ Taking control of the center. It's worth nothing that f4 also makes it harder for Black to carry out the desirable e5-move. }
7... a6
{ It's a bit surprising that this prophylactic move is on top of Stockfish's list. Black wants to play Nc6 when the endgame isn't as bad because Black can take on d8 with the knight. Nb5 would be the refutation in the previous note, but of course, this is not possible.   7...e5  Doesn't impress either.  8.fxe5  Bxe5  9.Qd2  Preparing to castle queenside.  9...Nc6  10.Nf3  Bg7  11.O-O-O  We are heading to a clearly better endgame due to our lead in development. By all means, you are free to keep the queens on the board with a move like 11. Bd3 or Qf2. The advantage is pretty decent there too.   7...Ne7  Was seen in Gara,T - Drljevic,L Riga 2017. White tried to be fancyand played 8. Nb5, but the natural  8.Nf3  was a lot better.  8...Nec6  9.e5  Black's opening has been a disaster. }
8. Nf3 Nxf3+
{ This looks best.  8...Nc6  was indeed the idea, but I think  9.Qe2  is really good for us.  g3-Bg2 is the way we will develop our pieces. }
9. Qxf3 Bd7 { Black is preparing himself to place the bishop on c6. } 10. Be2
{ This move is a huge improvement over Fernandez, D - Czebe, A Backa Palanka 2020 where White played  10.O-O-O?  This allowed  10...Bxc3  11.bxc3  Qe7  12.Bd4  f6  when Daniel was winning after  13.Qf2  . }
10... Bc6
{ 10...Bxc3  gives away the strong dark-squared bishop. This makes less sense here as our king will be safe on the kingside. The game could continue  11.bxc3  Nf6  12.Rd1  Qe7  13.Bd4  O-O-O  14.O-O  , when we are doing very well. }
11. Bc5
{ Preventing Black from castling while preventing Black from taking on c3 as we can simply take with the queen, attacking the rook on h8. }
11... Nf6 12. Qe3
{ Getting out of the pin. Now Black will have a hard time castling, giving us a clearly better position. }
