1. e4 g6 2. d4
{ As always we will take full control of the center if we get the chance. }
2... Bg7 { I'd say this move will be played against you 99/100 times... } 3.
Nc3
{ There are a bunch of different set-ups we can go for, but I think the knight move is the most critical option. The Main Line gives Black a plethora of options, which will all be covered in this chapter. }
3... a6
{ This cute little move gave me a serious headache as Black wants to move-order us out of our repertoire. }
4. h4
{ I eventually discovered that this move was the best to avoid any move-order nonsense. }
4... d5
{ The only alternative to the main move.   4...h5  A move a human makes from pure instinct, and in this case the instinct is correct.  5.Be3  We are now likely to transpose to different main lines. Which will be dealt with in a later chapter. }
5. Nxd5 { Black has two ways to chase away the knight. } 5... c6
{ is the worst way, when we get a great endgame after } 6. Ne3 Qxd4
{ 6...Bxd4  allows  7.h5  . } 7. Qxd4 Bxd4 8. h5
{ White is clearly better due to his space advantage. A plan forward could be Ne2 followed by f3-Nf4 or Nf3 followed by space grabbing moves like e5 or g4-g5. }
