1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. Nc3 d6 4. Be3 a6
{ The main tabiya of the Modern. Black aims to get quick play on the queenside, when the moves b5-Bb7-Nbd7-c5 will follow in some order. }
5. h4
{ After analyzing this line in great depth, I came to the conclusion that this was the most accurate move order that aligns with all our set-ups in the Pirc/ Modern coverage. }
5... h6 { Is another way for Black to defend against our h5-thrust. } 6. Qd2
{ Now h5 followed by f4 is a nice plan for us which is something Black has to be prepared for any time.   6.h5  g5  Is Black's main defensive idea, don't rush the attack. }
6... Nd7
{ 6...b5  won't make a difference, as we can see after  7.O-O-O  Nf6  8.f3  Bb7  9.Nh3  Nbd7  10.g4  with a classical attacking plan.   8.f3  Bb7  9.Nh3  Nbd7  10.g4  . We have now transposed to the main tabiya of the  h6  variation. }
7. O-O-O b5
{ Black has to gain counterplay somehow, and the way to do so is to expand on the queenside. }
8. Nh3
{ The knight is well placed here, as we want to play f3, defending the pawn on e4. From h3 it can also jump to f4 in some lines as we will see. Another factor is that the e2-square remains available to our knight on c3 in case Black plays b4, while our bishop on f1 can also be developed. }
8... Ngf6
{ Was played by the great Garry Kasparov against the World's best shogi player quite remarkable I know!, but it loses by force. }
9. e5 { This thrust works, due to } 9... Ng4 10. e6
{ Black's pawn structure gets destroyed and becomes an easy target for our pieces. }
10... fxe6 11. Nf4 { Attacking the lone soldiers on e6 and g6. } 11... Nf8 12.
Bd3 { Maintaining the pressure. } 12... Kf7
{ Defending the pawn on g6, won't work due to   12...Bb7  Black has to bite bullet and accept that the pawn on g6 falls.  13.Bxg6+  Nxg6  14.Nxg6  Rg8  15.f3  I don't think Black will survive this position in a practical game. Our moves are simple. h5-Ne2-Nf4 etc. }
13. h5 g5 14. Ng6 { Black's king is in Adam's clothing. } 14... Nxg6 15. Bxg6+
Kg8 16. f4
{ Black's extra pawn matters little as he is about to get destroyed on the kingside. }
