10. g4
{ Grabbing space on the kingside and preparing to kick away the knight on f6 by playing g5. }
10... Nb6
{ Freeing the d7-square for the knight on f6, so the g5-launch won't be as effective. }
11. a3 Nfd7
{ The most played move in the position is this one where is going for the typical c5-thrust. }
12. d5
{ The only move that can give Black problems is this move. The point is that we want to place a bishop on d4. }
