16. Nf4 c5 17. dxc6 Rxc6 18. Nfd5
{ The knight has reached the strong square on d5. Black tried } 18... Nxd5 19.
exd5 { Opening the e-file. } 19... Rc8 20. Bh3
{ Strong, but  20.f4  could be even stronger according to my engine. } 20...
Rc4 21. Qe3 Qc7 22. Rhe1 Nb6 23. f4
{ White's advantage had reached decisive heights already as Black has little counterplay for his poor king, and indeed, White eventually won in: Huber,M-Burmeister,F ICCF email 2017. }
