11... Qc7 12. f4
{ Taking control over the e5-square, so it's time for Black to finally take on d4. }
12... cxd4 13. Bxd4 Bxd4 14. Rxd4 Ngf6
{ Black has gotten pieces out, but he has poor control over the center, and little on the queenside. }
15. Qd2 O-O 16. Be2
{ We will soon play f5 and Rg3 where our attack looks dangerous. Black's attack, on the other hand, is nowhere to be seen. }
