[Black "Modern 4...a6 Conclusion"]
[Result "*"]

{ Conclusion: This chapter concluded the main tabiya of the Modern, with 4... a6. }
1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 { This move is almost always played. } 3. Nc3
{ Black has so many different ways to proceed that it's easy to get a headache. }
3... d6
{ is the main move, and indeed a very flexible one. Black can now decide whether or not he wants to take the game into a c6-structure, a6-structure or straight to the Pirc with Nf6. There were so many factors for me to consider and I really tore my hair out! }
4. Be3 a6 { The main focus of our chapter. } 5. h4
{ My recommendation where Black has three different ways of dodging our h5-break. }
5... h5
{ Easily the mainline and the primary focus in the chapter.   5...h6  is definitely better, with the idea of meeting h5 with g5. One really common plan for us is to play h5 at some point and then meeting Black's g5-move with f4.   5...Nf6  is the first one, but our analysis does conclude that our play after  6.h5  is more than adequate for the missing exchange. }
6. Nh3
{ A key flexible move where we will look to use the space left behind on g5 where the Knight will be quite annoying. }
*

