[Result "*"]

1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6
{ Here we have arrived at the opening sequence that defines the Pirc Defense. The opening tends to lead to exciting and complicated games, which is why the opening is often utilized by higher-rated players who badly needs a win with the black pieces. On top level you won't see this opening occur often, as White has numerous dangerous ways of fighting it, making the opening a risky choice. Just like most openings, White needs to know what he's doing in order to fight for an edge, so we must be prepared! }
4. Be3
{ We will play in similar fashion to the Modern Defense. The queen will head to d2 followed by O-O-O and Bh6, when Black will be under a vicious attack. Black has different set-ups here. He can either delay Bg7 by playing a6 or c6, he can play Bg7 and then a6 or c6, or he can simply castle. These different ways of playing have some subtle differences, as we soon shall see. }
4... Ng4
{ Once we have played Be3, it's always natural to fear this knight jump to g4. However, it doesn't lead anywhere, although it has been played in some games by the top player GM Shakh Mamedyarov. }
5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 g5
{ The only thing Black achieves by playing this move is to weaken his kingside drastically.   6...Bg7  The more solid attempt by Black simply gives us an easy game.  7.Be2!  The best move, developing while getting rid of the knight on g4.  7...Nf6  8.f4  Taking control of the center.  8...d5  Black's best bet, taking at least some control of the center.  9.e5  Ne4  10.Nf3  White's pawn center is powerful and secures him a clearly better position with castling to come next. }
7. Bg3 Bg7 8. Be2 Nf6 9. e5 Nfd7 10. h4
{ A strong move, utilizing the fact that Black is severely weakened on the kingside. }
10... dxe5 11. hxg5 hxg5
{ Loses by force, but Black's position is still awful after for example  11...Nc6  12.d5  Nd4  13.Qd2  hxg5  14.Rxh8+  Bxh8  15.Nf3  Nxf3+  16.Bxf3  . }
12. Rxh8+ Bxh8 13. Bc4 { Qh5 is now a deadly threat. } 13... Nf6 14. dxe5 Qxd1+
15. Rxd1 Nh5 16. Nd5
{ White is completely winning as  16...Kd8  loses a piece after  17.Nf6+  , when  Nxh5  will follow. }
*

