1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. Be3 c6 5. h3
{ We are taking control over the g4-square. From here, we plan to carry out the move f4 which will give us a better version of the Austrian Attack. Additionally, the possibility of playing g4 is there, although this occurs less frequently. }
5... Qb6
{ Attacking the b2-pawn is very uncommon, but it ranks high on the engine's list. }
6. Qc1
{ The most popular way to defend the b2-pawn, and also the most accurate. }
6... Bg7 7. f4 Na6
{ GM Timman continued like this, but was soon punished by the strong American prodigy, GM Sevian. }
8. a3
{ Taking control over the b4-square so we are not bothered by Nb4. We may even play b4 ourselves! }
8... Qa5 9. b4
