[Black "4...c6 (5...Qa5)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. Be3 c6 5. h3
{ We are taking control over the g4-square. From here, we plan to carry out the move f4 which will give us a better version of the Austrian Attack. Additionally, the possibility of playing g4 is there, although this occurs less frequently. }
5... Qa5
{ The Pirc specialist GM Onischuk has played this 'Czech-Pircy' move in some games against rather strong opposition. }
6. Bd3 { Guarding the pawn on e4 that was under attack. } 6... Nbd7 7. f4
{ The usual way of punishing Black's passive play is to take full control of the center. }
7... c5 8. Nf3 b5
{ Is a very tricky move and a typical resource Black has in these kinds of positions. The point is that our bishop can't take the b5-pawn, since it must watch over the e4-pawn.   8...Bg7  9.O-O  cxd4  10.Nxd4  Play is similar to what we saw in the Czech Pirc. Black is solid enough, but our central control and active pieces give us a clearly better game.  10...O-O  11.Be2!  This move is clever since the bishop will be better placed on the f3-square.  11...Nc5  12.Qd2  Defending the pawn on e4 with tactics.  12...Qc7  13.Bf3±  Our space advantage puts us in the driving seat. }
9. dxc5 { Is the right way to proceed. The play continues: } 9... b4 10. e5
{ Another very strong move, freeing the e4-square for the knight. } 10... dxe5
{ Happened in an e-mail game.  10...bxc3  is met by  11.b4!  This was necessary as Black was threatening to take on b2 with check.  11...Qc7  12.cxd6  exd6  13.exf6  Nxf6  Black's king has now been opened, which we will greatly utilize:  14.Bd4  Bg7  15.Qe2+  Not allowing Black to castle.  15...Qe7  16.Qxe7+  Kxe7  17.O-O  +-  Black has a vulnerable king and will also be down a pawn once we take the pawn on c3. }
11. fxe5 Nxc5 12. exf6 bxc3 13. b4
{ Once again this move is really strong, gaining an important tempo on Black's queen. }
13... Qxb4 14. O-O Nxd3 15. Qxd3
{ Black's position was hopeless as he was extremely undeveloped in: Hoexter,H -Aragones Cerezo,G ICCF email 2018. }
