{ The queen is headed to f2 where it will make it very difficult for Black to play c5.   11.e5  wasn't bad but still inferior to the text move in Sodoma, J - Mamedyarov, S Kallithea 2008. }
11... Bb7 12. Qf2 Nfd7
{ Black tried this in four games to desperately play c5, but it just doesn't work... And indeed, Black lost in all the games. }
13. a4
{ I like this move, but moves like  13.e5  and  13.f5  are objectively even stronger. }
13... b4
{ Black had to destroy his pawn structure by taking on a4. After this move he was soon busted after }
14. a5 bxc3 15. axb6 Nxb6 16. bxc3
{ Black's queenside play was completely gone in Mas,H - Garcia,J Subic Bay 2009, and Black was soon destroyed on the kingside as the counterplay was nowhere to be seen. }
