{ The exclamation mark might be a tad exaggerated, but this was the first time in the course that I was truly stuck and puzzled about which line to go for. Black's play is simple as he is ready to play on the queenside with b5 and Nbd7, while avoiding to castle kingside for now. The engine isn't so excited here either which is an important thing to highlight, and certainly an oddity in the lines with g6. }
6. g4
{ This move has only been played 60 times, so it's extremely uncommon.  6.Qd2  on the other hand has been seen over 4500 times, but as I showed in the informational, Black is fine. The plan behind  g4  is simple enough, as we want to launch a pawn storm towards the black king as quickly as possible.  6.a4  is a move the engine really likes which stops Black from playing b5. Definitely worth a look.  6.Nge2  is interesting too, with similar play as the text move. }
