13... Na6 14. Ne2 { The knight is headed to g3. } 14... Nb4
{ This forces us to take the bishop on f5.   14...O-O  is met by  15.Nxf5  with similar play. }
15. Nxf5 exf5 16. c3 Na6 17. Ng3
{ It's not easy to break through Black's defenses, but Black has a tough defensive job ahead of him as he needs to be very careful of sacrifices on the pawns on f5 or h5. Black also has practically no counterplay, which is tough for a human being. }
