6. g4 O-O { Has been tried here as well when I suggest going for } 7. Qd2
{ Same plan as usual with O-O-O-h4-Bh6 with an attack. } 7... Qa5
{ Starting with Qa5 is an interesting way for Black to play, as c5 is an additional option to Black's arsenal in some lines.   7...e5?!  Has been tried in over 70 games, but it's not good.  8.O-O-O  Nbd7  9.d5!  The refutation! Black has problems with the pawn on d6, which is why Black has played  9...c5  In almost every game I found. However, we are now free to wreak havoc on the kingside.  10.h4→  White had a devastating attack in four games here, one of them being Morev,I - Bessudnov,G Dagomys 2004. }
