{ The most precise way to proceed.  8.O-O-O?!  falls into Black's scheme after  8.. . c5!N when Black's pawns are moving with great velocity. The play can continue  9.d5  b5  10.Kb1  b4  11.Nce2  c4!  Black has a powerful attack, but the evaluation shows that he has no advantage. Anyway, this is of course not what we want... }
