10... Qd7
{ 10...f6  Is possible of course, when the game continues  11.exf6  Nxf6  12.O-O-O  Nc6   The necessary move. Slow moves like  12...a6  are met by  13.h4  when we get a powerful attack.  13.Nde2  N  A strong novelty. The knight is well placed on e2 where it can target the pawn on d5 with a subsequent knight jump to f4. I doubt Black will be able to save the pawn. h4 is a good move to include as well, since it will wreak havoc when it heads to h5. }
