{ It's so easy to play White. We will prepare a h5-break with f4 and Be2. The game can continue: }
14... c6
{ The best move by quite a lot, reason why I placed an exclam behind it. } 15.
Be2 { We keep going with our plan. } 15... d5
{ Blacks needs to open the position and trade queens, otherwise our attack will be too strong. }
16. f4 dxe4 17. Nxe4 Qxd2+ 18. Rxd2
{ Black has traded queens but not out of the woods yet due to Nf6+ being a nasty move to face. }
18... Red8 19. Nf6+ Kf8
{ Black has to give the h7-pawn as  19...Kh8  is curtains after  20.h5  when Black has placed himself in a mating net. }
20. Nxh7+ Ke7 21. Nf6 Rxd2 22. Kxd2 Rh8 23. h5
{ The resulting position is an endgame which is objectively winning for White as long as we take with the bishop when Black takes gxh5 @@StartBracket@@which is the only move, otherwise h6 comes@@EndBracket@@. }
