1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 Nbd7 4. f4
{ Just like in the Czech Pirc, we will take full control of the center. Now we are already threatening e5 which could lead to a disaster for Black. }
4... e5
{ Played almost every game, and for good reason. Black takes some central control and stops our e5-thrust. }
5. Nf3 exd4 6. Qxd4
{ Taking with the queen has been overwhelmingly the most common response, and indeed, it's the best move in the position as we want to castle queenside. }
6... Be7
{ Allows us to carry out the thematic break in the center.   6...Nc5?  Black has tried this in some games, when the refutation is rather straightforward.  7.Be3  We will castle queenside before we strike in the center.  7...g6  GM Beliavsky tried this move.  8.O-O-O  The strongest continuation. The hasty 8. e5 is good enough for a decisive advantage, but our text move is more precise.  8...Bg7  9.Qb4  e5 will come when Black is simply busted. }
7. e5 dxe5 8. fxe5 Bc5 { Most queen moves are strong here, but I like } 9. Qa4
{ In particular, pinning the knight on d7. } 9... Qe7 10. Be2
{ Making use of the fact that the knight can't take on e5 as it's pinned. }
10... Ng8 11. Bg5
{ Black's position was dreadful in Kristensen,K - Zachariassen,J Bornholm 2008. }
