1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5
{ This is the best and most common way to reach the Philidor Defense, named after the famous 18th century player Francois-André Danican Philidor. }
4. dxe5 dxe5 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 6. Bc4
{ The game has barely started, and an endgame is already here. } 6... Be6
{ I must admit that it's baffling to me that this move is the most played move in the position. Black willingly gives himself an inferior pawn structure, resulting in a position where only White can play for a win. }
7. Bxe6 fxe6 8. f3
{ Defending the pawn is the first matter of business. From here, Black has a wide range of different set-ups: }
8... Nbd7
{ Is another way for Black to play, but I think the knight is better placed on c6. }
9. Nh3 { Once again a strong move as we are aiming for the juicy d3-square. }
9... Bc5
{ Black can place the bishop on c5, and later d4. Note that 9... Bb4 is nothing to be worried about as we can play 10. Bd2.   9...Bd6  The typical plan, but I once again must stress that Black would have been better off placing the knight on c6.  10.Nf2  The typical maneuver - do I need to say more? :  10...Ke7   10...a6  can also be met by  11.b3  , when play will likely transpose.  11.b3  I like this move, aiming to place a knight or bishop on b2 in the near future.  11...a6  12.Nd3  Nb8!?  An interesting plan, Black regrets having put the knight on d7.  13.Be3   In this case we should keep the b2-square for the knight. In Bezgodov, A - Pridorozhni, A Khanty-Mansiysk 2013,  13.Bb2  happened, but after  13...Nc6  , White's advantage had decreased.  13...Nc6  14.Na4  b6  It's logical to take control over the c5-square.  15.Nab2  b5  Black tries to take control over the c4-square, now that the b2-knight can't jump to c5.  16.c3  Rhd8  17.Ke2  Black has hard times in sight. }
10. Nf2 { The knight is headed to d3. } 10... Ke7 11. Nd3 Bd4 12. Nd1
{ We will chase away the bishop on d4 with c3, and later place our knight on e3-c4. }
12... Rhd8 13. c3
{ An improvement over  13.N1f2  which happened in Petrosian, T - Sapaev, M Tashkent 2016. }
13... Bb6 14. Ne3 c6 15. Ke2
{ Black's position is depressing, and already lost according to my avid engine. }
