1. e4 Nc6
{ The 'Nimzowitch Defence,' a very rare breed. That being said, it is by far the best opening out of the rare openings out there. }
2. d4 d6
{ Might seem like a mouse-slip to you, but it's not. Black is provoking us into playing d5, when he has gotten a pawn structure that he desires. The price he has to pay for this is to be several tempos down a King's Indian, which can't be sound. }
3. d5 Ne5 4. f4
{ Gaining yet another tempo on the knight and increased central control. } 4...
Nd7 { Is the lesser evil, but that doesn't make the line good. } 5. Nf3 c6 6.
c4 { Our center is too strong. } 6... Ngf6
{ Has been tried, but Black will soon have issues as we will soon be able to carry out e5. }
7. Nc3 g6 { Suggested by my engine. } 8. e5 dxe5
{ 8...Ng8  9.Bd3  Bg7  Black tries to gain counterplay by battling our 'premature' e5-push. Unfortunately for him, we can simply sacrifice the pawn for overwhelming initiative.  10.Qe2  Qc7  11.O-O !  A strong pawn sacrifice which works tactically for us.  11...dxe5  12.fxe5  Nxe5  13.Bf4  Qb6+  14.Be3  Qc7  It seems like Black is surviving, but we have a great resource up our sleeve.  15.Nxe5  Bxe5  16.c5  We are aiming to play d6 which will give us a nice pathway towards Black's king. Additionally, we can place a bishop on c4 which will attack the f7-pawn.  16...Nf6  Black is almost on time to castle, but...  17.d6  Refutes Black's play.  17...exd6  18.Rxf6+-  A nice move which wins material and the game. }
9. fxe5 Ng4 { Is Black's best way to fight, but it doesn't work either. } 10.
Qd4 Ndxe5 { Black's piece sacrifice works tactically. } 11. Nxe5 Bg7 12. Bf4 g5
{ Black manages to win the piece back launching his kingside pawns against us. }
13. Bg3 f5
{ We can't escape the pin and save the piece, as Black will pay f4 next. Unfortunately for Black, things work out well for us in the end. }
14. Be2
{ A strong move, targeting the knight on g4. More importantly, the only way Black will win back the piece is to give up the pressure on our pawn on d5 by playing }
14... c5
{ Black wins back the piece, but with a kingside in jeopardy the position is pretty terrible after }
15. Qd2 Nxe5 16. Qxg5 Ng6 { And now, a very strong move is } 17. h4
{ The knight on g6 will be removed from its post and we will castle queenside.  17... Bf6 is met by 18.Qd2. Damn it feels good to have the white pieces... }
