[Black "2...e5 (4...d6)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nc6
{ The 'Nimzowitch Defence,' a very rare breed. That being said, it is by far the best opening out of the rare openings out there. }
2. d4 e5
{ Is one move Black can try in this position, but it seems like his position will become rather passive. }
3. d5
{ I think this is the best shot for an edge.  3.Nf3  is the Scotch of course, if you fancy that instead. }
3... Nce7 4. h4
{ This move makes it harder for Black to develop his pieces, as we can often meet g6 or Ng6 by h5. If Black plays h5 himself, the square on g5 will become rather weak. }
4... d6
{ I think it makes more sense to prepare f5 with this move in case Black wants to play the break early.   4...f5  Is a typical pawn break for Black to make.  5.Nc3  Nf6  This doesn't work out for Black due to a concrete resource.  6.exf5  Nxf5  7.g4!  Well spotted by Bocharov, who will soon play g5 and force the f6-knight back to g8.  7...Nd4  8.g5  Ng8  9.Nf3+-  Black's position was already lost in the game Bocharov,D - Ivaschenko,V Taganrog 2013. }
5. c4 { Taking control of the center. } 5... f5 6. Nc3 Nf6 7. Bd3
{ I like this approach by White. Black won't get any fun on the kingside, since it's so difficult to develop the pieces. }
7... f4
{ 7...g6  Doesn't work due to  8.Bg5  Bg7  9.h5+-  Black's position is in shambles. }
8. g3 { A strong move, breaking up Black's blockade of pawns. } 8... fxg3 9.
fxg3 Bg4 10. Be2
{ The bishop doesn't need to protect the e4-pawn any longer, so it's much better placed on e2. }
10... Qd7 11. Nf3 h6 { Preventing White from jumping to g5-e6. } 12. Be3 c5
{ A natural move for Black, stopping our queenside expansion. } 13. Nh2 Bxe2
14. Qxe2
{ White had played excellently in the opening in Fuchs, F - Porcher,E Neustadt an der Weinstrasse 2020. }
