[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "16. Nimzowitch's Defense (1...Nc6)"]
[Black "2...e5 (4...h5)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nc6
{ The 'Nimzowitch Defence,' a very rare breed. That being said, it is by far the best opening out of the rare openings out there. }
2. d4 e5
{ Is one move Black can try in this position, but it seems like his position will become rather passive. }
3. d5
{ I think this is the best shot for an edge.  3.Nf3  is the Scotch of course, if you fancy that instead. }
3... Nce7 4. h4
{ This move makes it harder for Black to develop his pieces, as we can often meet g6 or Ng6 by h5. If Black plays h5 himself, the square on g5 will become rather weak. }
4... h5 { An interesting try by Black is to stop our h5-launch. } 5. Be3
{ I prefer to place the bishop here, but it can also be placed on g5. } 5... d6
6. Nh3 { The knight can now head to g5 if Black tries to go for f5. } 6... g6
7. Qd2
{ The plan of O-O-O is strong, while the queen has other functions on d2 as well, since it can head to c3 in some lines. }
7... f5
{ 7...Nf6  8.f3  Bxh3  Black's best try is to get rid of the knight on h3.  9.Rxh3  Bg7  10.c4±  Black's position is in disarray. Our play is straightforward, and I can't really see what Black is doing as the plan of f5 will only weaken Black's king.   7...Bg7  can be met by  8.Ng5  provoking Black to play the move f6. Sooner or later he will play f5, when we will get the g5-square. }
8. Ng5 { Planning a pretty neat trap. } 8... f4
{ Loses to  8...Nf6  9.f3±  Leads to a clearly better position for us as we control both sides of the board and Black remains passive. }
9. Bxf4 { Our piece sacrifice will only be temporary. } 9... exf4 10. Qc3
{ Showing one advantage of having the queen on d2. } 10... Rh6 11. Bb5+
{ Black loses material by force. } 11... c6
{ 11...Bd7  is met by  12.Ne6  with Nxc7+ next. } 12. dxc6 bxc6 13. Bxc6+ Nxc6
14. Qxc6+ Bd7 15. Qd5
{ The knight can't defend the mate on f7, knight on g8 and rook on a8 simultaneously. }
