[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nc6
{ The 'Nimzowitch Defence,' a very rare breed. That being said, it is by far the best opening out of the rare openings out there. }
2. d4 d5
{ The exclam is well-deserved because this is Black's best bet and only path to 'equality.' Black's aim is to get decent control on the light squares and later attack our center with a move like f6. The engines are surprisingly optimistic on Black's behalf, which was quite sensational to me when I took a look. }
3. e5 Bf5
{ Surprisingly enough, the position now resembles an advanced Caro-Kann. One of the key differences is that Black's f6-break is more effective because of the knight on c6. The downside to having the knight on c6 is that the c5 pawn break can't happen yet as the knight stands in the way. }
4. c3
{ Like in the other lines, we will play this move solidifying our pawn structure. }
4... e6 5. Be2
{ This move is played very seldom. The point is that we aim to play similarly to lines we've already seen. f4-Nf3-Nbd2 etc. }
5... Nge7 { Has been played before, but it's inaccurate. } 6. Nd2
{ The best continuation.  6.f4?!  is too hasty, as Black can play  6...Bg6  , among other moves when  Nf5  will follow suit - justifying  Nge7  . }
6... f6 { Will of course be met by } 7. f4
{ As it is vital that we maintain our strong center. } 7... Qd7
{ Both games that I found proceeded with this move. } 8. Ngf3 Ng6 9. Nb3
{ This time,  9.g3  isn't as effective, as Black can play  9...h5  which is a bit annoying, with some counterplay. }
9... Be7 10. O-O O-O
{ Better than the risky  10...O-O-O  . Black can argue that the knight on  b3  puts a stop to some of our attacking chances. However, we can play 11. Be3 and move the knight back to  d2  in order to play  b4  . Black doesn't have enough play against our king to make good use of the extra tempos. }
11. Be3 Bg4
{ Black wants to ease the pressure and get rid of our knight on f3. } 12. Nbd2
{ I like this move, aiming to recapture with the knight in case Black decides to take. }
12... fxe5
{ Black has to do this before it's too late. Now, in Trump,L - Migl,D Bad Mergentheim 1988, Trump should have recaptured with the pawn! }
13. fxe5 Nf4 14. Bxf4 Rxf4
{ Black has obtained the bishop pair, but we still have the upper hand after }
15. h3 Bh5 16. Bd3
{ Our space advantage is more valuable than the bishop pair. } *

