14. Bxc4 e5 15. Nc3
{ This looks like the simplest approach to me. 15. d5 is the other alternative which I analyzed deeply, but I feel cruel requiring you to memorize so long lines :@@EndBracket@@ }
15... Nxd4 { Is Black's best try, which leads to a rather remarkable tactic. }
16. Nxd4 exd4 17. Rxe8+ Qxe8 18. Qxd4 f5
{ The logical move is to target our queen. } 19. Qd5
{ A great move which apparently leaves the knight hanging. } 19... Bxc3 20. Qd2
{ A remarkable move! Black can't take due to the mate on b2. } 20... Bg7
{ 20...Bf6  21.Re1  Qf8  22.Qxh6!  The tactics all work in our favor.  22...Bd7  23.Qc1↑  Black's exposed king gives us a dangerous initiative. }
21. Re1 Qd7 { The only move, as  21...Qf8??  loses due to  22.b5  . } 22. Qe3
{ Qe8 is coming. } 22... Ng8 23. Qe8 { And now the forced line goes: } 23...
Qxe8 24. Rxe8 Be6 25. Rxe6
{ Our bishop pair and active rook gives us excellent chances to squeeze out a win. }
