{ A move we constantly see in these positions, as it takes control of the open e-file. }
8... Nc6 9. h3
{ A strong move which limits the bishop on c8 and the knight on h6, since it controls the g4-square. }
9... f6
{ On most occasions Black has played this thematic move, but it turns out it's too rushed. If you have been paying attention, I am sure you now the answer that is...   9...Re8  Black can start with this move, but it should transpose to other variations.  10.Bf4  f6  Is a terrible move here due to the standard response  11.c4+-  Which was played in Wist, A -Goetz, A Bayern 2013.   10...Nf5  11.Nbd2  will surely transpose, unless Black does something outrageous. If that ends up being the case, I trust that you will be able to handle it! }
10. c4
{ YES! c4 attacks the pawn on d5 which will damage Black's center, making e5 a lot less potent. Black has tried different moves from this position: }
10... e6
{ I'm mentioning this move as it has been played by 5 games where Black was rated above 2250+ in all of them. }
11. Nc3 dxc4
{ Is no better   11...Nf7  Looks awful for Black after  12.cxd5!  exd5  13.Bc2!  The bishop is headed to b3 where it will target the d5-pawn.  13...Na5  I don't see what else Black can do.  14.Bf4  Simple chess.  14...Nc4  15.b3  Nb6  16.a4+-  With a5 @@StartBracket@@or Nb5 in case Black plays a5@@EndBracket@@ next, Black is completely lost. If I were him, I'd save myself the suffering and resign the game at once. }
12. Bxc4 Nf5 13. d5
{ The opening of the position will lead to a disaster for Black, as his pieces are terribly organized - much like Arsenal FC at the back. }
13... exd5 14. Nxd5 Kh8 15. Bf4 { The knight is headed to the c7-square. }
15... Nd6
{ White had played perfectly so far in Vokhidov, S - Weetik,V chess.com INT 2020, but here I suggest playing the simple }
16. Bb3 { Instead of playing  16.Nc7  . Black has no moves! } 16... Ne8
{ Prevents Nc7, but the position is in ruins after } 17. Qe2
{ With Rad1 coming. } *

