{ Our plan is no different. We aim to place our knight on the beautiful e5-square, with a dangerous attack. }
8... O-O 9. Bg5
{ This looks like the best approach.  9.Ne5?!  is inaccurate now, as Black has the strong resource  9...Ne4!  After  10.Nxc6  bxc6  11.Bxe4  dxe4  12.Rxe4  c5  , Black has sufficient compensation for the pawn.  9.Nbd2  can be played, but I prefer to avoid  9...Qc7  10.Qe2  Nd7  , which is kind of annoying as we can't jump to  e5  anymore! That being said, we are better here too after something like  11.Nf1  . }
9... h6 { The automatic reaction when Bg5 is played. } 10. Bh4 Qb6
{ I stumbled upon this intriguing move in my analysis.   10...Be7  The most popular move in the position, but it's not very challenging.  11.Nbd2  Nd7  Black is out of the pin, but the loss of tempos makes it not worth it. Compare this to the line we just took a look at, 10... Qb6.  12.Bxe7  Qxe7  13.Re3!  A strong move which prepares the Alekhine Battery in the e-file.  13...b6  14.Qe2  Bb7  15.Re1  Rad8  16.h3±  We are in complete control. }
11. Na3
{ This funny move is the right way to go!  11.Bxf6  looks good, but in fact Black is fine after  11...gxf6   11.Qc2  looks logical, but  11...Nh5  is an annoying response. Black is preparing  g5  followed by  Nxg3  . Black can also play  Nf4  . }
11... Nh5
{ Is still possible, of course.   11...Bxa3  And now  12.Bxf6!  The absence of Black's dark-squared bishop ads much more venom to our attack.  12...gxf6  13.bxa3  Qd8  Black has to bring the queen to the defense.  14.Re3!  A thematic and strong attacking move.  14...Kg7  15.Nh4  f5  Forced.  16.Rg3+  Kh7  17.Rh3  Qf6  18.Nf3→  We have a very dangerous attack with ideas like Qd2-Qf4. We should move the king out of the g-file before we push g2-g4. }
12. Rb1 { The simplest, as there will be no Qxb2 to worry about. } 12... Nf4
{ 12...Bxa3  Looks decent for Black, but the dark-squared bishop is superior to our knight.  13.bxa3  Qa5?  A poor move, but I want to showcase the beautiful refutation. 13... Qc7 is necessary, which we can meet with 14. c4! We will open the position when our bishop pair will be very strong.  14.Ne5  Nf4  15.Bf6+-  A fantastic move that wins immediately due to our incredibly powerful attack.  15...Ng6  is apparently the best defense, which we can meet with  16.Qh5!  The line goes  16...Ncxe5  17.dxe5  , when Re3-g3 comes with a lethal attack. }
13. Bc2
{ We have a nice initiative. It's not easy to tell what Black should do. Bg3 followed by Ne5 could come soon, or the pawn storm c4-c5-b4. }
