{ Now that we can't exploit Black's poor queen placement on e7, or take the hanging pawn on b7, we must go for an endgame. }
11... Qe7 12. Nh3
{ Black won't keep the extra pawn for long. Now he has to make a decision on whether to ignore our knight jump or destroy our pawn structure with f3. }
12... f3 13. gxf3 Nf6
{ I don't think Black should wait with grabbing our queen. } 14. Qe3
{ A pretty subtle move. We're simply dodging Black's Qxe2.   14.Nd2  makes more sense, but after  14...Qxe2  Black is doing better than the text. }
14... O-O-O { And now, we decide to trade queens } 15. Qxe7 Bxe7 16. Nd2
{ We're going to play f4-Nf3-O-O-O-Ne5 with a pretty comfortable position. This is one of those cases where Black is doing fairly okay, but it's not very fun OTB. }
