[Black "3...Be7 (4...c5)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Be7
{ The last sideline we must consider is this move which looks very peculiar indeed. To me it looks like a way for Black to avoid the most dangerous lines in the Classical Variation I am indeed talking about our move 4. Bg5 while confusing the opponent. However, the move has a major flaw which is clearly seen after our response. }
4. e5
{ This is the only way to punish Black's set-up as the knight is locked in place on g8. }
4... c5 5. Qg4
{ This is a typical reaction when Black has no protection over the pawn on g7 as we are forcing him to make a concession. }
5... g5
{ This move is Black's best bet to create some problems for us as the positions that occur are quite tricky. Black will soon follow up with h5 which will give him some space on the kingside. The aggressive approach has its downside though, as it does make Black more vulnerable on the kingside. }
6. dxc5 h5 { Black gets some space on the kingside and pushes our queen away. }
7. Qg3 Nh6
{ Black develops his pieces with great speed, with Nf5 coming soon. Our pawn on e5 can also be targeted easily by the black pieces, so we must be careful about how we proceed. }
8. Nb5
{ Attack is the best defense. Our knight will be well-placed on the d6-square. }
8... Nf5 9. Qc3 { We must keep the c5-pawn under protection. } 9... d4 10. Qa3
{ Again, the pawn has to be protected. } 10... Nc6 11. h4
{ A strong pawn sacrifice which aims to remove Black's control of the f4-square. }
11... Nxh4
{ 11...gxh4  is just a terrible version of the main line as Black doesn't get the extra exchange. }
12. Nd6+
{ 12.Bd2  is also strong, but I like our chances in the upcoming endgame. }
12... Kf8 13. Rxh4
{ A beautiful positional move which removes Black's counterplay against our center. }
13... gxh4 14. Bf4
{ It's simple to play our position. Black is very cramped, which is tough for a human. }
14... Qa5+ { Black's best chance is to head into an endgame. } 15. Qxa5 Nxa5
16. b4 Nc6 17. a3 { Look at our strong pawn chain! } 17... Bxd6 18. cxd6
{ The endgame looks like pure misery for Black. } *

[Event "?"]
