1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3
{ We have spent this chapter covering some of the most unusual stuff Black has at his disposal. There are two moves that fit in this category of 'unusual species,' namely 3... Nc6 & 3... Be7. There's more to these moves than what meets the eye, be prepared! }
3... Nc6 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. e5 Ne4 6. Ne2
{ Our strategy should be to play around the knight on e4. } 6... Na5
{ Black switches plans and opts for the c5-break. } 7. Ng3
{ In order to create an attack against Black's king, we should get rid of the e4-knight. }
7... c5 8. Bd3 Nxg3 9. fxg3
{ It's always strange to take with the f-pawn instead of the h-pawn, but in this case the open file is a highly useful asset to our attack. }
9... cxd4 10. O-O
{ Black already needs to stay alert on the dangers looming in the f-file. }
10... Be7 11. Nh4
{ A fantastic move which improves on  11.Nxd4  which I suggested on chess24. The point is that we want to play  Qg4  or  Qh5  , creating decisive threats against Black's king. The knight on  h4  contributes more than the knight on  d4  , hence the evaluation difference. }
11... O-O { Black's king doesn't have enough defences to play this move. } 12.
Qg4
{ Black has to deal with the threat of Bh6 which turns out to be an impossible task.   12...Kh8  is met by  13.Qh5  , when we will sacrifice our way through.   12...f6  is met by  13.exf6  , when a capture on  f6  follows  @@StartBracket@@if Black captures with the rook@@EndBracket@@ followed by Qh5, when we are once again breaking through.   12...g6  is met by  13.Bh6  , when Black can't move the rook due to the f7-pawn hanging after  Qf3  . }
12... Qc7 13. Bxh7+ { 13.Bh6  is the same, but this looks more epic. } 13...
Kxh7 14. Bh6 { A fantastic move. } 14... Qxe5
{ Black's best out of three losing moves.   14...Kxh6  Loses to  15.Rxf7!  g5  And now there's only one way to win, but it's a mate in three.  16.Nf5+  exf5  17.Qh3+  Kg6  18.Qh7  Very beautiful.   14...gxh6  Is no better, when the solution is the same:  15.Rxf7+  Rxf7  16.Qg6+  Kh8  17.Qxf7+-  Unfortunately for Black, the queen on c7 remains unprotected so Black loses the queen after Bxh4. }
15. Rae1
{ Black will be down decisive material and can pretty much resign the game. } *

