{ Black's best attempt for counterplay, played almost exclusively. } 11. c3
Qxc5 12. O-O-O { Our plan hasn't changed! } 12... a5
{ A logical way to create some complications is to launch the a-pawn forward.   12...Rd8?!  Allows the nice tactic  13.Bxf6  Bxf6  14.Bxh7+  Kxh7  15.Rxd8  Bxd8  16.Qd3++-  Which wins a pawn. Black's position looks already lost if you ask me. White has 9.5/10 from this position, so apparently my theory is kind of accurate. }
