{ It looks like Black has tricked us as the c3-pawn is hanging, but it's not the case due to }
15. Kxe2 Nxc3+ 16. Ke3 { A fantastic move! Black's knight on c3 is doomed. }
16... O-O
{ Black intends Rc8 but it doesn't work out!   16...Nd1+!?  Is a funny trick. We don't need to take and allow Qc3+ though!  17.Kd3  Qb4  Black's scariest move, intending Nc6 with an attack on our pawn on d4.  18.Rb1!  Nc6  Black keeps having tactics, but it's time to put an end to it once and for all!  19.Qxc6+  bxc6  20.Rxb4  Nf2+  21.Ke3  Nxh1  22.Ba3+-  Black loses the knight on h1 after we move the rook to b1 and the f1-bishop. There's no need to worry about a move like Rb8 either, as we can just dodge with a move like Rc1. }
17. Bd2 Rc8 18. Rc1 b5
{ Black's almost in time to play b4 to save the knight, but.. . } 19. Qb2
{ Wins, as we can meet b4 with } 19... b4 20. a3
{ The tactics work us for us. axb4 is now a threat. } 20... bxa3
{ And now we have } 21. Rxc3 axb2 22. Rxc8+ Kh7 23. Bd3+ g6 24. Bxa5
{ With a completely winning position. } *

