[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "23. French Defense (1...e6) Mainlines"]
[Black "4...Be7 (6...f6)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Be7
{ The last branch of the line! This has been the most popular response by Black, and is thus the main tabiya of the complex. }
5. e5
{ Black targets our pawn, so we must advance.  5.Bxf6  is possible, but harmless for Black. }
5... Nfd7 6. h4
{ This pawn sacrifice known as the Alekhine-Chatard Attack, is the most challenging way to meet 4. Be7.   6.Bxe7  , White's most common try, is more of a positional approach where White is typically aiming for the good knight against Black's poor bishop. However, this is less dangerous than our move,  6.h4!  , where Black's route towards equality is incredibly narrow. Black has numerous alternatives which we will explore before delving into the mainlines, so buckle up! Some are better than others, but none of them seem satisfactory... }
6... f6
{ Is a typical move to make when playing the French, but in this position it doesn't work for concrete reasons. }
7. Qh5+ { Refutes Black's dreams of removing our initiative. } 7... g6
{ 7...Kf8  might be objectively best, but it's not challenging at all. Black's king is in the center when the position is quite open! The game goes  8.exf6  Nxf6  , and here we have many alternatives. I like  9.Qf3  c5  10.dxc5  , when  O-O-O  will soon follow. I found a pretty nice game that went  10...Nbd7  11.O-O-O  Nxc5  12.Nh3  Bd7  13.Nf4  Bc6  14.Bxf6  Bxf6  15.Ne4  Bxb2+  16.Kb1  Qb6  17.Nxd5+  Bf6+  18.Nxb6  Bxe4  19.Qa3  and Black resigned in Jones-Riley corr 1982. }
8. exf6 Nxf6 { Black has avoided the endgame in almost every game I found. } 9.
Qe2
{ Black's position is already lost according to my machine. We have excellent pressure against the pawn on e6 and great attacking chances. The game can continue }
9... c5 10. dxc5 Nc6 11. O-O-O O-O 12. Nh3
{ Nf4  comes with devastating effect. Black has nothing on the queenside either, as we can respond calmly with  12...Qa5  Kb1  in case Black attempts to get active against our King. }
