[White "23. French Defense (1...e6) Mainlines"]
[Black "4...Be7 (6...Nc6 3)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Be7
{ The last branch of the 3... Nf6-line! Black gets out of the pin by simply moving the bishop in between. This has been the most popular response by Black, and is thus the main tabiya of the 4. Bg5-line. }
5. e5
{ Black targets our pawn, so we must advance. 5. Bxf6 is possible, but harmless for Black. }
5... Nfd7 6. h4 { This pawn sacrifice known as the Alekhine-Chatard Attack. }
6... Nc6
{ Is a pretty interesting sideline. Black will someday play f6, when the knight on c6 contributes by controlling the e5-square. This will make the desired pawn-break e6-e5 easier to achieve. Another detail is that Black has an additional option in Nxe7 if we decide to capture Black's bishop. }
7. Qd2 { The right square for the queen. } 7... f6
{ Black goes directly for the thematic f6. The downside of this move, as I have already pointed out, is how it gives us a square on e5 and Black a backward pawn on e6. }
8. exf6 Nxf6 9. O-O-O O-O
{ Black's position looks like a Tarrasch-gone-wrong @@StartBracket@@those of you who have experience with 3. Nd2 will get it@@EndBracket@@. }
10. f4
{ We're taking full control over the square on e5. Black's position looks positionally horrible. }
10... a6
{ Was seen in Alexiadis,H - Korniotis,F Achaia 2017. There are many good reactions here, for example   10...h6  Only helps us out, as  11.Bxf6  Is a move we would like to play at some point.  11...Bxf6  12.Nf3+-  Black's lost positionally. The plan g3-Bh3-Re1 is really tough to meet. }
11. Nf3 b5 12. Bd3 { Simple chess, developing our pieces. } 12... b4
{ Is Black's idea, but it doesn't do much. } 13. Na4 Bd6 14. h5
{ It's time to start an attack! } 14... h6 15. Bh4
{ Black can't do much else than watch how we assault him on the kingside. }
15... Qe8 16. Bg6 Qd7 17. Bxf6 Rxf6 18. Ne5
{ Is just a perfect display of chess harmony. Look at the dominance! We'll take with the d-pawn when Black captures the knight with the bishop. }
