1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Be7 5. e5 Nfd7 6. h4 Bxg5
{ This time on the menu of our 1. e4 restaurant is the Alekhine- Chatard Attack Accepted. A courageous choice, but objectively the right one. That being said, the path forward is very narrow for Black... One has to be incredibly well prepared, hence why 4... dxe4 has taken more and more over. }
7. hxg5 Qxg5 8. Nh3
{ Black has to make an incredibly important decision on where to place the queen. }
8... Qg6
{ Is almost never played, and for good reason as the queen is far too vulnerable on g6. }
9. Qd2 { The simplest. We're going to play Ng5 followed by O-O-O and Bd3. }
9... Qh5
{ Black dodges Ng5.   9...a6  is met by  10.Ng5  , while  9...c5  is met by  10.Nb5  . }
10. g4 { Black's queen is lured out so we can attack it with our forces. }
10... Qxg4 11. Ng5 { Black's queen is struggling to find available squares. }
11... h6 12. Be2
{ It's an important detail that Black can't take on g5 due to the hanging rook on h8. }
12... Qf5 13. O-O-O
{ Rdg1 is coming when Black's queen won't make it.   13...Rg8  makes sense to dodge  Bd3  , but it's met by  14.Rdg1  as Black's queen is trapped after  14...hxg5  15.Rxg5  Qxf2  16.Nd1  . }
