[Round "?"]
[White "23. French Defense (1...e6) Mainlines"]
[Black "4...Be7 (6...Bxg5 8...Qe7 6)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Be7 5. e5 Nfd7 6. h4 Bxg5
{ This time on the menu of our 1. e4 restaurant is the Alekhine- Chatard Attack Accepted. A courageous choice, but objectively the right one. That being said, the path forward is very narrow for Black... One has to be incredibly well prepared, hence why 4... dxe4 has taken more and more over. }
7. hxg5 Qxg5 8. Nh3
{ Black has to make an incredibly important decision on where to place the queen. }
8... Qe7
{ This is by far the most logical and popular move. Unfortunately for Black, it is a bad one. }
9. Qg4 g6 { The most natural way to face the threat of Qxg7. } 10. Ng5
{ We're provoking additional concessions in Black's camp. } 10... h5
{ Now that we've seen that  10...h6  doesn't work out for Black due to the Nxf7-tactics, Black has no choice but to go for this move.  h5 has other downsides as it gives us a fantastic outpost on g5, while the pawn on h5 can easily be targeted by the means of g4. }
11. Qf4 Nc6
{ Is a better plan. Black is planning to get his pieces out by playing Nb6 and Bd7. }
12. O-O-O Nb6
{ 12...Nf8?  Is just awful.  13.g4!  Gives Black serious problems as we're opening the position.  13...Nh7  Is Black's idea, but it's too slow.  14.Nxh7  Rxh7  15.Bg2  And Black has no good way to meet Bxd5.  15...Bd7  16.Bxd5+-  Black's position was pure garbage in Lobanov,S -Golikov,D St Petersburg 2019. }
13. Rh3
{ The thematic rook swing is very strong here, as Black has trouble guarding the pawn on f7.   13.g4  is less strong due to  13...Bd7  when Black escapes quickly to the queenside with the king. }
13... Bd7 14. Rf3 Rf8
{ Looks like a highly unfortunate necessity.   14...O-O-O  Is met by the tactical trick  15.Nxf7!  Rdf8  16.Nxh8!   Important! Not  16.Qf6?  when we're in trouble after  16...Qe8  .  16...Rxf4  And our point is shown after  17.Nxg6!  Qg5  18.Nxf4±  Was a beautiful dance with the knight in Avalboev,S -Trubchaninov,A Sochi 2016. White is close to winning due to the extra pawn. It's only a matter of technique. }
15. Nh7 Rh8 16. Nf6+ { And Black's king loses the right to castle. } 16... Kd8
17. Rh3
{ Our rook has done its job on f3, so it's time that we start opening the position with g4. White is clearly better. }
