[Black "3...Bb4 (4...Qd7 2)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Bb4
{ We have finally arrived to the main bulk of our coverage on the French, and our very last topic to cover for Part 1! This is the Winawer Variation, named after Szymon Winawer and popularized later in the 1940s by the greats Nimzowitch and Botvinnik. After 3... Bb4, Black pins the knight and thus attacks the pawn on e4 so we're forced to make a decision in the center. }
4. e5
{ This is by far the most challenging move against the Winawer. We're gaining additional space while we're also limiting Black's knight on g8 as it can no longer jump to f6.   Black's standard way of playing is to challenge our center right away with the standard French-move  4...c5  , but the topic for this chapter is to take a look at what happens in case Black refrains from the usual procedure. }
4... Qd7 5. h4
{ This is a move you will see constantly throughout the entire coverage of Winawer. With h4 our rook can join the game by swinging to h3-g3, while we also aim to get a very nice pawn structure with h5 later on. Note that Qg4 is more dangerous with h4 included, as g6 is met by the very unpleasant h5. }
5... c5 6. a3 Ba5 { I suggest meeting this retreat with } 7. Bd2 cxd4 8. Nb5
{ Is our idea. } 8... Bc7
{ Black is attacking our pawn on e5, and with Nc6 coming, things do not look so simple. However, I found the nice move }
9. Qh5 { That nicely guards the pawn. } 9... Nc6 10. Nf3 Nge7 11. O-O-O
{ Black is struggling with his lack of coordination and development. For example: }
11... a6 12. Nxc7+
{ Grabbing the bishop is best, although we still have a huge edge after  12.Nbxd4  . }
12... Qxc7 13. Qg4 { Forcing Black to make an unpleasant choice. } 13... O-O
{ Is the lesser of evils, but Black's king is quite vulnerable after } 14. Bd3
Ng6 15. Qh5 { Otherwise the pawn on e5 falls. } 15... Bd7 16. Rde1
{ With the attacking plan of Rh3-Rg3-Qg4-h5 which looks hard to stop. Black is not fast enough on the queenside.   The best move is  16...Nce7  with the idea of Bb5, when it's important that we grab the pawn with  17.Nxd4  . }
