14... dxc4
{ Should lead to  14...Ncxd4  , but I figured out that Black has an extra option in }
15. Be4 c3 { 15...Ncxd4  transposes. } 16. Bg5
{ The position on the board looks chaotic, but we'll be able to neutralize Black's play with a few accurate moves. }
16... Rg6 17. gxf5 exf5 18. Bd5+
{ We don't take on c6 right away, as we want to make sure that Black's rook is trapped on g6. }
18... Be6 19. Bxc6 Qxc6 20. O-O
{ We have everything under control and plan to play Ne5 or Nh4 next.   20...Qe4  is the only way to keep the rook, but it doesn't save the game as we're winning after  21.Rae1  Qg4+  22.Qxg4  fxg4  23.Nh4  Rxg5  24.Rxe6  , when our extra piece decides. }
