16. Rf4 { The concrete approach. The calmer 16. Kd1 looks really good too. }
16... Qxc2 17. Rxf7+ Ke8 18. Ra1 Nc5
{ This move loses the game, but it's rather tricky. If Black plays  18...Rg8  , I think  19.a4  is a strong response, with  Ba3  coming.   18...Nf5  Is objectively the best try, leading to a forced line where we'll have to sacrifice our queen!  19.Rb7  Rf8  Black doesn't really have other moves, as g4 or Qg4 comes really quickly.  20.Ne2  We're forced to guard the pawn on c3, so we're unable to get our queen out of the way in time. But don't fret, as our position is still excellent after the queen sac.  20...Nd6  21.exd6  Rxf3  22.gxf3  Our rook on b7 is incredibly strong while black's pieces are rather passive. Our pawn on d6 also contributes greatly to our pressure.  22...Rd8  Black can't do much else, otherwise Rxg7 comes.  23.Rxa7  Nb8  24.Rxg7  Nc6  25.Bf4+-  I don't think Black will survive this position in the long run, as our forces are incredibly strong. Black needs to play  25...Rd7  , when we have really strong pressure after  26.Rg8+  Kf7  27.Rc8  Nd8  28.Kf1  . }
