[White "27. Model Games"]
[Black "9. Rodriguez, Luis vs. Larsen, Arne Walther"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. f3 Bg7 5. Be3 c6 6. g4 b5 7. a3 Nbd7 8. h4 h5
9. g5 Nh7 10. Nge2 O-O 11. Bg2 Nb6 12. b3 a5 13. O-O d5
{ I have my doubts of this move, but Black is essentially hoping that it won't be possible to break through.   13...Qc7  Looks more natural to me, when I think we have a nice game after  14.Ng3⩲  With f4 or Qd2 coming next. White's position looks much easier to handle. }
14. e5
{ Rodriguez pushes the pawn, giving Black better control over the light squares in exchange for more space. The question is if White can break through... }
14... Re8
{ Giving the f8-square to the knight.   14...Bf5  15.Ng3  e6  Is possible, but after  16.a4  b4  17.Nce2±  I think White will have all the fun. A capture on f5 will come, when we can open the queenside with c3 or c4. }
15. Ng3 e6
{ Everything is blocked, so how to break through? Let's see how Rodriguez does it... }
16. f4 a4
{ This move looks strange for a human, but Black wants to get some play in the a-file or the c4-square in case of b3-b4. It's not a good move, however...   16...Ba6  Looks more natural to me, but I do think Black is still in trouble after  17.Rf2±  When there's only a matter of time before a sacrifice on h5 comes. }
17. Nce2
{ White returns the favor and doesn't exploit Black's inaccuracy.   17.b4+-  Would have been the way, when White has all the time in the world to prepare the sac on h5, similar to the game. }
17... Re7
{ Strange is the only word I can use to describe this move...   17...axb3  Was necessary, but even after  18.cxb3±  Black is still in big trouble. Nc1-Nd3-Rc1 may come, or a sacrifice on h5. Both plans look promising if you ask me. }
18. b4
{ Finally. Black has no counterplay and can only watch as White demolishes his defense. }
18... Ba6 19. Nxh5 { Perhaps a bit too early, but it does work. } 19... gxh5
20. Ng3 Nc4 21. Bc1
{ Black's knight reaches its destination, but it only looks pretty on the outside. In reality, it does nothing on c4. }
21... Kh8 22. Qxh5 Qg8 23. c3 { White has all the time in the world. } 23...
Raa7 24. Ra2 { The other rook joins the attack. } 24... Qe8 25. Rf3 Qg8 26. Bf1
Bc8 27. Bd3 { White slowly improves his pieces before the final blow. } 27...
Rac7 28. Rg2 Re8 29. Ne2 Ree7 30. g6 { It's time... } 30... fxg6 31. Bxg6 Bf8
32. Rfg3 Rg7 33. f5 exf5 34. Bh6
{ White breaks through. It was only a matter of time. } 34... Nxa3 35. Bxg7+
Rxg7 36. Nf4 { Black resigned, as his engine showed mate in 9. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
