[White "27. Model Games"]
[Black "17. Hudak, Dusan vs. Bernal Caamano, Jose Luis"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Bb4 5. e5 h6 6. Bd2 Bxc3 7. bxc3 Ne4 8. Qg4
g6 9. Bc1 c5 10. Bd3 Nxc3 11. dxc5 Qa5 12. Bd2 Qxc5 13. Ne2
{ As stated in the chapter, White has obtained a fantastic Wing-Gambit as Black is severely struggling on the dark squares due to the absence of the dark-squared bishop. Let's see how Hudak increases his advantage. }
13... Ne4
{ Black prefers to give back the queen in exchange for one of the bishops. }
14. Bxe4 dxe4 15. O-O
{ White can ignore the hanging pawn on e5 as it's completely untouchable due to Bc3. }
15... Nc6
{ The most natural move in the world, but it makes things even worse for Black.   15...Bd7  Was better, as Black has the resource Bc6 in case White continues like in the game.  16.Rfd1  Nc6  17.Rab1  O-O-O  Seems like a natural way the game could proceed, when I found a semi-forced sequence:  18.Qxe4  Qxe5  19.Qxe5  Nxe5  20.Bc3  Bb5  21.Nf4  f6  22.Bxe5  fxe5  23.Nxg6  Black is on the verge of losing. Perhaps it's already too late... }
16. Nc3
{ This is a very strong move, utilizing perfectly how weak Black is on the dark squares. }
16... Qxe5
{ 16...Nxe5  Won't help Black after  17.Qg3  Black's camp is too exposed. In the event of  17...f5  18.Na4  Qb5  19.Rab1  Qxa4  20.Qxe5  Wins immediately.  20...Rg8  21.Rxb7+-  Is a nice trick. }
17. Nxe4 { White is ready to play Bc3 which will really hurt. } 17... Qg7
{ This move makes little sense to me.   17...h5  Is the most logical approach, when Black is busted after  18.Qh4  f5  19.Nf6+  Kf7  20.Bg5+-  As the king is far too weak. Black has no good way to face Rad1 and Rfe1. }
18. Bb4 { A very strong move, intending Nd6+. } 18... Nxb4 19. Nd6+ Kf8 20.
Qxb4 Kg8 21. Ne8
{ Black's defenses fall apart due to the invasion on the dark squares. } 21...
Qe5 22. Rfe1 a5 23. Qa3 Qd4 24. Qe7 b5 25. Qc7
{ The point of this move is to prevent Black from playing Ra7! } 25... b4 26.
Rad1 Qc3 27. Qe7 { White's forces are finally invading the camp. } 27... h5 28.
Re3 Qxc2 { Black has nothing else due to Rd8. } 29. Ree1
{ The c-file has been opened... } 29... Qc3 30. Rc1
{ Black loses material so a resignation is appropriate. A really nice win by Hudak who greatly showed how dangerous the dark-squares superiority can become. }
