[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "27. Model Games"]
[Black "18. Hofer, Rudolf vs. Goreczny, Grzegorz"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Bb4 5. e5 h6 6. Bd2 Bxc3 7. bxc3 Ne4 8. Bc1
Nxc3 9. Qg4 g6 10. Bd3 c5 11. dxc5 Qa5 12. Bd2 Qa4 13. Qf3 Ne4 14. Bxe4 dxe4
15. Qb3 Qa6 16. Ne2 Bd7 17. c4 Ba4 18. Qc3 Nd7 19. O-O Nxc5 20. Be3 b6 21. Ng3
Bc6 22. Rad1
{ Black is under pressure as White is planning to infiltrate on d6 with Bxc5 followed by Rd6. }
22... Nb7
{ Black prevents the idea.   22...Nd3  Should be met by  23.f3  When Black loses the pawn on e4. I analyzed a long sequence:  23...O-O-O  24.fxe4  Nc5  25.Rd6  Rxd6  26.exd6  Rd8  27.Rxf7  Rxd6  28.Bf4  e5  29.Qxe5  Rd1+  30.Nf1  Rxf1+  31.Kxf1  Qxc4+  32.Kg1  Qxf7  33.Qb8+  Kd7  34.Qd6+  Ke8  35.Qxc6+  Nd7  36.Bxh6  Qxa2  37.Qxg6++-  When White should win the ending with accurate play.   22...Rc8  Is initially liked by my engine, but after  23.Bxc5  bxc5  24.Rd6±  Black's position looks terrible. }
23. Qc1
{ This move is excellent, as Hofer wants to force Black into making a concession. }
23... Qa5
{ This move is pretty much forced, intending to meet Bxh6 with Qxe5. } 24. h3
{ A calm move that improves the position as the king gets a safe spot on h2. }
24... h5
{ Black wants to push away the knight on g3 with h4, but it's too weakening.   24...Rd8  Is Black's best defense.  25.Rxd8+  Kxd8  Black can't allow c4-c5.  26.Bxh6  Qxe5  27.Bf4  Qc5  28.Qc3  e5  29.Bxe5  Re8  30.Bf4±  Black's position is very unpleasant, but it's not over yet. }
25. c5
{ This move is very strong. Its purpose is to interfere with Black's queen, as it will no longer target the pawn on e5. This will allow the dark-squared bishop to enter the beautiful outpost on f6 via g5. }
25... Nxc5 26. Rd6
{ A strong intermezzo. The idea is significantly less effective if Black is able to block the rook with Bd5. }
26... Bd5 27. Bg5 Kf8 28. Bf6 { The bishop enters. } 28... Rh7 29. Ne2
{ The knight is headed to c3 or f4 where it can remove the rock standing on d5. }
29... Kg8 30. Nf4 Qxa2 31. Nxd5 exd5
{ And now comes the star move of the game... } 32. e6
{ Black's terrible control over the dark squares leads to his demise. } 32...
Nxe6 33. Rxe6 fxe6 34. Qg5 { White enters the camp. } 34... Kf8 35. Qxg6 Rf7
36. Qh6+ Ke8 37. Qh8+ Kd7 38. Qxa8 Rxf6
{ It looks like Black is out of the woods, but White has another piece he can bring to the attack... }
39. Rc1 { The threat of Qb7# is decisive. } 39... Qxf2+ 40. Kh1 Qf1+
{ Black has no other choice.   40...d4  Creates an escape route for the king, but after  41.Qxa7+  Kd6  42.Qxb6+  Ke5  43.Qb8+  Kf5  44.Rc5+  Kg6  45.Qg8+  Kh6  46.Rg5!  Qf1+  47.Kh2  Qf4+  48.Rg3  Black has no defense! A pretty cute line... }
41. Rxf1 Rxf1+ 42. Kh2
{ With the aid from an engine, there really was never any doubt that Hofer would convert the ending. }
42... Ra1 43. Qh8 Ra4 44. Qxh5 e3 45. Qe2 Re4 46. g4 Kd6 47. Kg1 d4 48. g5 Re5
49. h4 Ke7 50. Kf1 a5 51. Qc4 Rd5 52. Qc7+ Rd7 53. Qf4 Rd5 54. Ke1 a4 55. Qc7+
Rd7 56. Qxb6 a3 57. Qa5 d3 58. Qxa3+ Kf7 59. Kd1 e2+ 60. Kd2 e5 61. Qc3
{ A fantastic game! } *

[Event "?"]
